75 /// This takes an arbitrary SelectionDAG as input and ----
76 /// hacks on it until the target machine can handle it. This involves ----
77 /// eliminating value sizes the machine cannot handle (promoting small sizes to ----
78 /// large sizes or splitting up large values into small values) as well as ----
79 /// eliminating operations the machine cannot handle. ----
80 /// ----
81 /// This code also does a small amount of optimization and recognition of idioms ----
82 /// as part of its processing. For example, if a target does not support a ----
83 /// 'setcc' instruction efficiently, but does support 'brcc' instruction, this ----
84 /// will attempt merge setcc and brc instructions into brcc's. ----
85 class SelectionDAGLegalize { ----

87 const TargetLowering &TLI; ----

93 ----
94 /// A set of all the nodes updated during legalization. ----
95 SmallSetVector *UpdatedNodes; ----
96 ----

260 /// Return a vector shuffle operation which ----
261 /// performs the same shuffle in terms of order or result bytes, but on a type ----
262 /// whose vector element type is narrower than the original shuffle type. ----
263 /// e.g. <0, 1, 0, 1> -> v8i16 <0, 1, 2, 3, 0, 1, 2, 3> ----
264 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ShuffleWithNarrowerEltType( 0
265 EVT NVT, EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue N1, SDValue N2, ----
266 ArrayRef Mask) const { ----
267 unsigned NumMaskElts = VT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
268 unsigned NumDestElts = NVT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
269 unsigned NumEltsGrowth = NumDestElts / NumMaskElts; 0
270 ----
271 assert(NumEltsGrowth && "Cannot promote to vector type with fewer elts!"); 0
272 ----
273 if (NumEltsGrowth == 1) 0
274 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(NVT, dl, N1, N2, Mask); 0
275 ----
276 SmallVector NewMask; 0
277 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumMaskElts; ++i) { 0
278 int Idx = Mask[i]; 0
279 for (unsigned j = 0; j != NumEltsGrowth; ++j) { 0
280 if (Idx < 0) 0
281 NewMask.push_back(-1); 0
282 else ----
283 NewMask.push_back(Idx * NumEltsGrowth + j); 0
284 } ----
285 } ----
286 assert(NewMask.size() == NumDestElts && "Non-integer NumEltsGrowth?"); 0
287 assert(TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(NewMask, NVT) && "Shuffle not legal?"); 0
288 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(NVT, dl, N1, N2, NewMask); 0
289 } 0

294 SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandConstantFP(ConstantFPSDNode *CFP, bool UseCP) { 0
295 bool Extend = false; 0
296 SDLoc dl(CFP); 0
297 ----
298 // If a FP immediate is precise when represented as a float and if the ----
299 // target can do an extending load from float to double, we put it into ----
300 // the constant pool as a float, even if it's is statically typed as a ----
301 // double. This shrinks FP constants and canonicalizes them for targets where ----
302 // an FP extending load is the same cost as a normal load (such as on the x87 ----
303 // fp stack or PPC FP unit). ----
304 EVT VT = CFP->getValueType(0); 0
305 ConstantFP *LLVMC = const_cast(CFP->getConstantFPValue()); 0
306 if (!UseCP) { 0
307 assert((VT == MVT::f64 || VT == MVT::f32) && "Invalid type expansion"); 0
308 return DAG.getConstant(LLVMC->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt(), dl, 0
309 (VT == MVT::f64) ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32); 0
310 } ----
311 ----
312 APFloat APF = CFP->getValueAPF(); 0
313 EVT OrigVT = VT; 0
314 EVT SVT = VT; 0
315 ----
316 // We don't want to shrink SNaNs. Converting the SNaN back to its real type ----
317 // can cause it to be changed into a QNaN on some platforms (e.g. on SystemZ). ----
318 if (!APF.isSignaling()) { 0
319 while (SVT != MVT::f32 && SVT != MVT::f16 && SVT != MVT::bf16) { 0
320 SVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(SVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy - 1); 0
321 if (ConstantFPSDNode::isValueValidForType(SVT, APF) && 0
322 // Only do this if the target has a native EXTLOAD instruction from ----
323 // smaller type. ----
324 TLI.isLoadExtLegal(ISD::EXTLOAD, OrigVT, SVT) && 0
325 TLI.ShouldShrinkFPConstant(OrigVT)) { 0
326 Type *SType = SVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0
327 LLVMC = cast(ConstantExpr::getFPTrunc(LLVMC, SType)); 0
328 VT = SVT; 0
329 Extend = true; 0
330 } ----
331 } ----
332 } ----
333 ----
334 SDValue CPIdx = ----
335 DAG.getConstantPool(LLVMC, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
336 Align Alignment = cast(CPIdx)->getAlign(); 0
337 if (Extend) { 0
338 SDValue Result = DAG.getExtLoad( 0
339 ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, OrigVT, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx, 0
340 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), VT, 0
341 Alignment); ----
342 return Result; 0
343 } ----
344 SDValue Result = DAG.getLoad( 0
345 OrigVT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx, 0
346 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), Alignment); 0
347 return Result; 0
348 } 0

350 /// Expands the Constant node to a load from the constant pool. ----
351 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandConstant(ConstantSDNode *CP) { 0
352 SDLoc dl(CP); 0
353 EVT VT = CP->getValueType(0); 0
354 SDValue CPIdx = DAG.getConstantPool(CP->getConstantIntValue(), 0
355 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0

357 SDValue Result = DAG.getLoad( 0

363 /// Some target cannot handle a variable insertion index for the ----
364 /// INSERT_VECTOR_ELT instruction. In this case, it ----
365 /// is necessary to spill the vector being inserted into to memory, perform ----
366 /// the insert there, and then read the result back. ----
367 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::PerformInsertVectorEltInMemory(SDValue Vec, 0
368 SDValue Val, ----
369 SDValue Idx, ----
370 const SDLoc &dl) { ----
371 SDValue Tmp1 = Vec; 0
372 SDValue Tmp2 = Val; 0
373 SDValue Tmp3 = Idx; 0
374 ----
375 // If the target doesn't support this, we have to spill the input vector ----
376 // to a temporary stack slot, update the element, then reload it. This is ----
377 // badness. We could also load the value into a vector register (either ----
378 // with a "move to register" or "extload into register" instruction, then ----
379 // permute it into place, if the idx is a constant and if the idx is ----
380 // supported by the target. ----
381 EVT VT = Tmp1.getValueType(); 0
382 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType(); 0
383 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VT); 0
384 ----
385 int SPFI = cast(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex(); 0
386 ----
387 // Store the vector. ----
388 SDValue Ch = DAG.getStore( 0
389 DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Tmp1, StackPtr, 0
390 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI)); 0
391 ----
392 SDValue StackPtr2 = TLI.getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VT, Tmp3); 0
393 ----
394 // Store the scalar value. ----
395 Ch = DAG.getTruncStore( 0
396 Ch, dl, Tmp2, StackPtr2, ----
397 MachinePointerInfo::getUnknownStack(DAG.getMachineFunction()), EltVT); 0
398 // Load the updated vector. ----
399 return DAG.getLoad(VT, dl, Ch, StackPtr, MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack( 0
400 DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI)); 0
401 } ----
402 ----
403 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandINSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Vec, SDValue Val, 0
404 SDValue Idx, ----
405 const SDLoc &dl) { ----
406 if (ConstantSDNode *InsertPos = dyn_cast(Idx)) { 0
407 // SCALAR_TO_VECTOR requires that the type of the value being inserted ----
408 // match the element type of the vector being created, except for ----
409 // integers in which case the inserted value can be over width. ----
410 EVT EltVT = Vec.getValueType().getVectorElementType(); 0
411 if (Val.getValueType() == EltVT || 0
412 (EltVT.isInteger() && Val.getValueType().bitsGE(EltVT))) { 0
413 SDValue ScVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, 0
414 Vec.getValueType(), Val); ----
415 ----
416 unsigned NumElts = Vec.getValueType().getVectorNumElements(); 0
417 // We generate a shuffle of InVec and ScVec, so the shuffle mask ----
418 // should be 0,1,2,3,4,5... with the appropriate element replaced with ----
419 // elt 0 of the RHS. ----
420 SmallVector ShufOps; 0
421 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) 0
422 ShufOps.push_back(i != InsertPos->getZExtValue() ? i : NumElts); 0
423 ----
424 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(Vec.getValueType(), dl, Vec, ScVec, ShufOps); 0
425 } 0
426 } ----
427 return PerformInsertVectorEltInMemory(Vec, Val, Idx, dl); 0
428 } ----

461 ----

463 // If this target supports 64-bit registers, do a single 64-bit store. ----
464 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(MVT::i64)) { 0

470 ----
471 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(MVT::i32) && !ST->isVolatile()) { 0
472 // Otherwise, if the target supports 32-bit registers, use 2 32-bit ----
473 // stores. If the target supports neither 32- nor 64-bits, this ----
474 // xform is certainly not worth it. ----

476 SDValue Lo = DAG.getConstant(IntVal.trunc(32), dl, MVT::i32); 0
477 SDValue Hi = DAG.getConstant(IntVal.lshr(32).trunc(32), dl, MVT::i32); 0
478 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian()) 0

480 ----

482 ST->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo); ----
483 Ptr = DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Ptr, TypeSize::Fixed(4), dl); 0
484 Hi = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Hi, Ptr, 0
485 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(4), 0

550 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legalizing truncating store operations\n"); 0

559 // storing an integral number of bytes. For example, promote ----

568 // If not storing a power-of-2 number of bits, expand as two stores. ----
569 assert(!StVT.isVector() && "Unsupported truncstore!"); 0

572 assert(LogStWidth < 32); 0
573 unsigned RoundWidth = 1 << LogStWidth; 0
574 assert(RoundWidth < StWidthBits); 0
575 unsigned ExtraWidth = StWidthBits - RoundWidth; 0
576 assert(ExtraWidth < RoundWidth); 0
577 assert(!(RoundWidth % 8) && !(ExtraWidth % 8) && 0
578 "Store size not an integral number of bytes!"); ----
579 EVT RoundVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), RoundWidth); 0
580 EVT ExtraVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), ExtraWidth); 0
581 SDValue Lo, Hi; 0
582 unsigned IncrementSize; ----

584 if (DL.isLittleEndian()) { 0
585 // TRUNCSTORE:i24 X -> TRUNCSTORE:i16 X, TRUNCSTORE@+2:i8 (srl X, 16) ----
586 // Store the bottom RoundWidth bits. ----
587 Lo = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, Value, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(), 0
588 RoundVT, ST->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo); ----
589 ----
590 // Store the remaining ExtraWidth bits. ----
591 IncrementSize = RoundWidth / 8; 0
592 Ptr = DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(Ptr, TypeSize::Fixed(IncrementSize), dl); 0

595 DAG.getConstant(RoundWidth, dl, 0

598 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize), 0
599 ExtraVT, ST->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo); ----
600 } else { ----
601 // Big endian - avoid unaligned stores. ----
602 // TRUNCSTORE:i24 X -> TRUNCSTORE:i16 (srl X, 8), TRUNCSTORE@+2:i8 X ----
603 // Store the top RoundWidth bits. ----
604 Hi = DAG.getNode( 0
605 ISD::SRL, dl, Value.getValueType(), Value, ----
606 DAG.getConstant(ExtraWidth, dl, 0
607 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(Value.getValueType(), DL))); 0

609 ST->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo); ----
610 ----
611 // Store the remaining ExtraWidth bits. ----
612 IncrementSize = RoundWidth / 8; 0
613 Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, Ptr.getValueType(), Ptr, 0
614 DAG.getConstant(IncrementSize, dl, 0
615 Ptr.getValueType())); ----

617 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize), 0
618 ExtraVT, ST->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo); ----
619 } ----
620 ----
621 // The order of the stores doesn't matter. ----
622 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo, Hi); 0
623 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Result); 0
624 } else { ----
625 switch (TLI.getTruncStoreAction(ST->getValue().getValueType(), StVT)) { 0
626 default: llvm_unreachable("This action is not supported yet!"); 0
627 case TargetLowering::Legal: { 0
628 EVT MemVT = ST->getMemoryVT(); 0
629 // If this is an unaligned store and the target doesn't support it, ----
630 // expand it. ----
631 if (!TLI.allowsMemoryAccessForAlignment(*DAG.getContext(), DL, MemVT, 0
632 *ST->getMemOperand())) { 0
633 SDValue Result = TLI.expandUnalignedStore(ST, DAG); 0
634 ReplaceNode(SDValue(ST, 0), Result); 0
635 } ----
636 break; 0
637 } ----
638 case TargetLowering::Custom: { 0
639 SDValue Res = TLI.LowerOperation(SDValue(Node, 0), DAG); 0
640 if (Res && Res != SDValue(Node, 0)) 0
641 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Res); 0
642 return; 0
643 } ----
644 case TargetLowering::Expand: 0
645 assert(!StVT.isVector() && 0
646 "Vector Stores are handled in LegalizeVectorOps"); ----
647 ----
648 SDValue Result; 0
649 ----
650 // TRUNCSTORE:i16 i32 -> STORE i16 ----
651 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(StVT)) { 0
652 Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, StVT, Value); 0
653 Result = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Value, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(), 0
654 ST->getOriginalAlign(), MMOFlags, AAInfo); ----
655 } else { ----
656 // The in-memory type isn't legal. Truncate to the type it would promote ----
657 // to, and then do a truncstore. ----

662 DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, Value, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(), StVT, 0

666 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Result); 0

730 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legalizing extending load operation\n"); 0
731 EVT SrcVT = LD->getMemoryVT(); 0
732 TypeSize SrcWidth = SrcVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
733 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags(); 0

735 ----
736 if (SrcWidth != SrcVT.getStoreSizeInBits() && 0
737 // Some targets pretend to have an i1 loading operation, and actually ----
738 // load an i8. This trick is correct for ZEXTLOAD because the top 7 ----
739 // bits are guaranteed to be zero; it helps the optimizers understand ----
740 // that these bits are zero. It is also useful for EXTLOAD, since it ----
741 // tells the optimizers that those bits are undefined. It would be ----
742 // nice to have an effective generic way of getting these benefits... ----
743 // Until such a way is found, don't insist on promoting i1 here. ----
744 (SrcVT != MVT::i1 || 0
745 TLI.getLoadExtAction(ExtType, Node->getValueType(0), MVT::i1) == 0
746 TargetLowering::Promote)) { ----

1370 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandExtractFromVectorThroughStack(SDValue Op) { 0
1371 SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0); 0
1372 SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(1); 0
1373 SDLoc dl(Op); 0
1374 ----
1375 // Before we generate a new store to a temporary stack slot, see if there is ----
1376 // already one that we can use. There often is because when we scalarize ----
1377 // vector operations (using SelectionDAG::UnrollVectorOp for example) a whole ----
1378 // series of EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT nodes are generated, one for each element in ----
1379 // the vector. If all are expanded here, we don't want one store per vector ----
1380 // element. ----
1381 ----
1382 // Caches for hasPredecessorHelper ----
1383 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
1384 SmallVector Worklist; 0
1385 Visited.insert(Op.getNode()); 0
1386 Worklist.push_back(Idx.getNode()); 0
1387 SDValue StackPtr, Ch; 0
1388 for (SDNode *User : Vec.getNode()->uses()) { 0
1389 if (StoreSDNode *ST = dyn_cast(User)) { 0
1390 if (ST->isIndexed() || ST->isTruncatingStore() || 0
1391 ST->getValue() != Vec) 0
1392 continue; 0
1393 ----
1394 // Make sure that nothing else could have stored into the destination of ----
1395 // this store. ----
1396 if (!ST->getChain().reachesChainWithoutSideEffects(DAG.getEntryNode())) 0
1397 continue; 0
1398 ----
1399 // If the index is dependent on the store we will introduce a cycle when ----
1400 // creating the load (the load uses the index, and by replacing the chain ----
1401 // we will make the index dependent on the load). Also, the store might be ----
1402 // dependent on the extractelement and introduce a cycle when creating ----
1403 // the load. ----
1404 if (SDNode::hasPredecessorHelper(ST, Visited, Worklist) || 0
1405 ST->hasPredecessor(Op.getNode())) 0
1406 continue; 0
1407 ----
1408 StackPtr = ST->getBasePtr(); 0
1409 Ch = SDValue(ST, 0); 0
1410 break; 0
1411 } ----
1412 } ----
1413 ----
1414 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType(); 0
1415 ----
1416 if (!Ch.getNode()) { 0
1417 // Store the value to a temporary stack slot, then LOAD the returned part. ----
1418 StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VecVT); 0
1419 Ch = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Vec, StackPtr, 0
1420 MachinePointerInfo()); ----
1421 } ----
1422 ----
1423 SDValue NewLoad; 0
1424 Align ElementAlignment = ----
1425 std::min(cast(Ch)->getAlign(), 0
1426 DAG.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign( 0
1427 Op.getValueType().getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()))); 0
1428 ----
1429 if (Op.getValueType().isVector()) { 0
1430 StackPtr = TLI.getVectorSubVecPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VecVT, 0
1431 Op.getValueType(), Idx); ----
1432 NewLoad = DAG.getLoad(Op.getValueType(), dl, Ch, StackPtr, 0
1433 MachinePointerInfo(), ElementAlignment); ----
1434 } else { ----
1435 StackPtr = TLI.getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VecVT, Idx); 0
1436 NewLoad = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, Op.getValueType(), Ch, StackPtr, 0
1437 MachinePointerInfo(), VecVT.getVectorElementType(), ----
1438 ElementAlignment); ----
1439 } ----
1440 ----
1441 // Replace the chain going out of the store, by the one out of the load. ----
1442 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(Ch, SDValue(NewLoad.getNode(), 1)); 0
1443 ----
1444 // We introduced a cycle though, so update the loads operands, making sure ----
1445 // to use the original store's chain as an incoming chain. ----
1446 SmallVector NewLoadOperands(NewLoad->op_begin(), ----
1447 NewLoad->op_end()); 0
1448 NewLoadOperands[0] = Ch; 0
1449 NewLoad = 0
1450 SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(NewLoad.getNode(), NewLoadOperands), 0); 0
1451 return NewLoad; 0
1452 } 0
1453 ----
1454 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandInsertToVectorThroughStack(SDValue Op) { 0
1455 assert(Op.getValueType().isVector() && "Non-vector insert subvector!"); 0
1456 ----
1457 SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0); 0
1458 SDValue Part = Op.getOperand(1); 0
1459 SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(2); 0
1460 SDLoc dl(Op); 0
1461 ----
1462 // Store the value to a temporary stack slot, then LOAD the returned part. ----
1463 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType(); 0
1464 EVT SubVecVT = Part.getValueType(); 0
1465 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VecVT); 0
1466 int FI = cast(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex(); 0
1467 MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo = ----
1468 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI); 0
1469 ----
1470 // First store the whole vector. ----
1471 SDValue Ch = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Vec, StackPtr, PtrInfo); 0
1472 ----
1473 // Then store the inserted part. ----
1474 SDValue SubStackPtr = ----
1475 TLI.getVectorSubVecPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VecVT, SubVecVT, Idx); 0
1476 ----
1477 // Store the subvector. ----
1478 Ch = DAG.getStore( 0
1479 Ch, dl, Part, SubStackPtr, ----
1480 MachinePointerInfo::getUnknownStack(DAG.getMachineFunction())); 0
1481 ----
1482 // Finally, load the updated vector. ----
1483 return DAG.getLoad(Op.getValueType(), dl, Ch, StackPtr, PtrInfo); 0
1484 } 0
1485 ----
1486 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandVectorBuildThroughStack(SDNode* Node) { 0
1487 assert((Node->getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR || 0
1488 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS) && ----
1489 "Unexpected opcode!"); ----
1490 ----
1491 // We can't handle this case efficiently. Allocate a sufficiently ----
1492 // aligned object on the stack, store each operand into it, then load ----
1493 // the result as a vector. ----
1494 // Create the stack frame object. ----
1495 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1496 EVT MemVT = isa(Node) ? VT.getVectorElementType() 0
1497 : Node->getOperand(0).getValueType(); 0
1498 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
1499 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VT); 0
1500 int FI = cast(FIPtr.getNode())->getIndex(); 0
1501 MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo = ----
1502 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI); 0
1503 ----
1504 // Emit a store of each element to the stack slot. ----
1505 SmallVector Stores; 0
1506 unsigned TypeByteSize = MemVT.getSizeInBits() / 8; 0
1507 assert(TypeByteSize > 0 && "Vector element type too small for stack store!"); 0
1508 ----
1509 // If the destination vector element type of a BUILD_VECTOR is narrower than ----
1510 // the source element type, only store the bits necessary. ----
1511 bool Truncate = isa(Node) && 0
1512 MemVT.bitsLT(Node->getOperand(0).getValueType()); 0
1513 ----
1514 // Store (in the right endianness) the elements to memory. ----
1515 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Node->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1516 // Ignore undef elements. ----
1517 if (Node->getOperand(i).isUndef()) continue; 0
1518 ----
1519 unsigned Offset = TypeByteSize*i; 0
1520 ----
1521 SDValue Idx = DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(FIPtr, TypeSize::Fixed(Offset), dl); 0
1522 ----
1523 if (Truncate) 0
1524 Stores.push_back(DAG.getTruncStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, 0
1525 Node->getOperand(i), Idx, 0
1526 PtrInfo.getWithOffset(Offset), MemVT)); ----
1527 else ----
1528 Stores.push_back(DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Node->getOperand(i), 0
1529 Idx, PtrInfo.getWithOffset(Offset))); ----
1530 } ----
1531 ----
1532 SDValue StoreChain; 0
1533 if (!Stores.empty()) // Not all undef elements? 0
1534 StoreChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Stores); 0
1535 else ----
1536 StoreChain = DAG.getEntryNode(); 0
1537 ----
1538 // Result is a load from the stack slot. ----
1539 return DAG.getLoad(VT, dl, StoreChain, FIPtr, PtrInfo); 0
1540 } 0
1541 ----
1542 /// Bitcast a floating-point value to an integer value. Only bitcast the part ----
1543 /// containing the sign bit if the target has no integer value capable of ----
1544 /// holding all bits of the floating-point value. ----
1545 void SelectionDAGLegalize::getSignAsIntValue(FloatSignAsInt &State, 0
1546 const SDLoc &DL, ----
1547 SDValue Value) const { ----
1548 EVT FloatVT = Value.getValueType(); 0
1549 unsigned NumBits = FloatVT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
1550 State.FloatVT = FloatVT; 0
1551 EVT IVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NumBits); 0
1552 // Convert to an integer of the same size. ----
1553 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(IVT)) { 0
1554 State.IntValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, IVT, Value); 0
1555 State.SignMask = APInt::getSignMask(NumBits); 0
1556 State.SignBit = NumBits - 1; 0
1557 return; 0
1558 } ----
1559 ----
1560 auto &DataLayout = DAG.getDataLayout(); 0
1561 // Store the float to memory, then load the sign part out as an integer. ----
1562 MVT LoadTy = TLI.getRegisterType(MVT::i8); 0
1563 // First create a temporary that is aligned for both the load and store. ----
1564 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(FloatVT, LoadTy); 0
1565 int FI = cast(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex(); 0
1566 // Then store the float to it. ----
1567 State.FloatPtr = StackPtr; 0
1568 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction(); 0
1569 State.FloatPointerInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI); 0
1570 State.Chain = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, Value, State.FloatPtr, 0
1571 State.FloatPointerInfo); ----
1572 ----
1573 SDValue IntPtr; 0
1574 if (DataLayout.isBigEndian()) { 0
1575 assert(FloatVT.isByteSized() && "Unsupported floating point type!"); 0
1576 // Load out a legal integer with the same sign bit as the float. ----
1577 IntPtr = StackPtr; 0
1578 State.IntPointerInfo = State.FloatPointerInfo; 0
1579 } else { ----
1580 // Advance the pointer so that the loaded byte will contain the sign bit. ----
1581 unsigned ByteOffset = (NumBits / 8) - 1; 0
1582 IntPtr = 0
1583 DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(StackPtr, TypeSize::Fixed(ByteOffset), DL); 0
1584 State.IntPointerInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI, 0
1585 ByteOffset); ----
1586 } ----
1587 ----
1588 State.IntPtr = IntPtr; 0
1589 State.IntValue = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, DL, LoadTy, State.Chain, IntPtr, 0
1590 State.IntPointerInfo, MVT::i8); ----
1591 State.SignMask = APInt::getOneBitSet(LoadTy.getScalarSizeInBits(), 7); 0
1592 State.SignBit = 7; 0
1593 } ----
1594 ----
1595 /// Replace the integer value produced by getSignAsIntValue() with a new value ----
1596 /// and cast the result back to a floating-point type. ----
1597 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::modifySignAsInt(const FloatSignAsInt &State, 0
1598 const SDLoc &DL, ----
1599 SDValue NewIntValue) const { ----
1600 if (!State.Chain) 0
1601 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, State.FloatVT, NewIntValue); 0
1602 ----
1603 // Override the part containing the sign bit in the value stored on the stack. ----
1604 SDValue Chain = DAG.getTruncStore(State.Chain, DL, NewIntValue, State.IntPtr, 0
1605 State.IntPointerInfo, MVT::i8); ----
1606 return DAG.getLoad(State.FloatVT, DL, Chain, State.FloatPtr, 0
1607 State.FloatPointerInfo); 0
1608 } ----
1609 ----
1610 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandFCOPYSIGN(SDNode *Node) const { 0
1611 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1612 SDValue Mag = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1613 SDValue Sign = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1614 ----
1615 // Get sign bit into an integer value. ----
1616 FloatSignAsInt SignAsInt; 0
1617 getSignAsIntValue(SignAsInt, DL, Sign); 0
1618 ----
1619 EVT IntVT = SignAsInt.IntValue.getValueType(); 0
1620 SDValue SignMask = DAG.getConstant(SignAsInt.SignMask, DL, IntVT); 0
1621 SDValue SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, IntVT, SignAsInt.IntValue, 0
1622 SignMask); ----
1623 ----
1624 // If FABS is legal transform FCOPYSIGN(x, y) => sign(x) ? -FABS(x) : FABS(X) ----
1625 EVT FloatVT = Mag.getValueType(); 0
1626 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FABS, FloatVT) && 0
1627 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FNEG, FloatVT)) { 0
1628 SDValue AbsValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::FABS, DL, FloatVT, Mag); 0
1629 SDValue NegValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, DL, FloatVT, AbsValue); 0
1630 SDValue Cond = DAG.getSetCC(DL, getSetCCResultType(IntVT), SignBit, 0
1631 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, IntVT), ISD::SETNE); 0
1632 return DAG.getSelect(DL, FloatVT, Cond, NegValue, AbsValue); 0
1633 } ----
1634 ----
1635 // Transform Mag value to integer, and clear the sign bit. ----
1636 FloatSignAsInt MagAsInt; 0
1637 getSignAsIntValue(MagAsInt, DL, Mag); 0
1638 EVT MagVT = MagAsInt.IntValue.getValueType(); 0
1639 SDValue ClearSignMask = DAG.getConstant(~MagAsInt.SignMask, DL, MagVT); 0
1640 SDValue ClearedSign = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MagVT, MagAsInt.IntValue, 0
1641 ClearSignMask); ----
1642 ----
1643 // Get the signbit at the right position for MagAsInt. ----
1644 int ShiftAmount = SignAsInt.SignBit - MagAsInt.SignBit; 0
1645 EVT ShiftVT = IntVT; 0
1646 if (SignBit.getScalarValueSizeInBits() < 0
1647 ClearedSign.getScalarValueSizeInBits()) { 0
1648 SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MagVT, SignBit); 0
1649 ShiftVT = MagVT; 0
1650 } ----
1651 if (ShiftAmount > 0) { 0
1652 SDValue ShiftCnst = DAG.getConstant(ShiftAmount, DL, ShiftVT); 0
1653 SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, ShiftVT, SignBit, ShiftCnst); 0
1654 } else if (ShiftAmount < 0) { 0
1655 SDValue ShiftCnst = DAG.getConstant(-ShiftAmount, DL, ShiftVT); 0
1656 SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, ShiftVT, SignBit, ShiftCnst); 0
1657 } ----
1658 if (SignBit.getScalarValueSizeInBits() > 0
1659 ClearedSign.getScalarValueSizeInBits()) { 0
1660 SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MagVT, SignBit); 0
1661 } ----
1662 ----
1663 // Store the part with the modified sign and convert back to float. ----
1664 SDValue CopiedSign = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MagVT, ClearedSign, SignBit); 0
1665 return modifySignAsInt(MagAsInt, DL, CopiedSign); 0
1666 } 0
1667 ----
1668 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandFNEG(SDNode *Node) const { 0
1669 // Get the sign bit as an integer. ----
1670 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1671 FloatSignAsInt SignAsInt; 0
1672 getSignAsIntValue(SignAsInt, DL, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
1673 EVT IntVT = SignAsInt.IntValue.getValueType(); 0
1674 ----
1675 // Flip the sign. ----
1676 SDValue SignMask = DAG.getConstant(SignAsInt.SignMask, DL, IntVT); 0
1677 SDValue SignFlip = ----
1678 DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, DL, IntVT, SignAsInt.IntValue, SignMask); 0
1679 ----
1680 // Convert back to float. ----
1681 return modifySignAsInt(SignAsInt, DL, SignFlip); 0
1682 } 0
1683 ----
1684 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandFABS(SDNode *Node) const { 0
1685 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
1686 SDValue Value = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1687 ----
1688 // Transform FABS(x) => FCOPYSIGN(x, 0.0) if FCOPYSIGN is legal. ----
1689 EVT FloatVT = Value.getValueType(); 0
1690 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, FloatVT)) { 0
1691 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstantFP(0.0, DL, FloatVT); 0
1692 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, DL, FloatVT, Value, Zero); 0
1693 } ----
1694 ----
1695 // Transform value to integer, clear the sign bit and transform back. ----
1696 FloatSignAsInt ValueAsInt; 0
1697 getSignAsIntValue(ValueAsInt, DL, Value); 0
1698 EVT IntVT = ValueAsInt.IntValue.getValueType(); 0
1699 SDValue ClearSignMask = DAG.getConstant(~ValueAsInt.SignMask, DL, IntVT); 0
1700 SDValue ClearedSign = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, IntVT, ValueAsInt.IntValue, 0
1701 ClearSignMask); ----
1702 return modifySignAsInt(ValueAsInt, DL, ClearedSign); 0
1703 } 0
1704 ----
1705 void SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC(SDNode* Node, 0
1706 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
1707 Register SPReg = TLI.getStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore(); 0
1708 assert(SPReg && "Target cannot require DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC expansion and" 0
1709 " not tell us which reg is the stack pointer!"); ----
1710 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
1711 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1712 SDValue Tmp1 = SDValue(Node, 0); 0
1713 SDValue Tmp2 = SDValue(Node, 1); 0
1714 SDValue Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1715 SDValue Chain = Tmp1.getOperand(0); 0
1716 ----
1717 // Chain the dynamic stack allocation so that it doesn't modify the stack ----
1718 // pointer when other instructions are using the stack. ----
1719 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, 0, 0, dl); 0
1720 ----
1721 SDValue Size = Tmp2.getOperand(1); 0
1722 SDValue SP = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, SPReg, VT); 0
1723 Chain = SP.getValue(1); 0
1724 Align Alignment = cast(Tmp3)->getAlignValue(); 0
1725 const TargetFrameLowering *TFL = DAG.getSubtarget().getFrameLowering(); 0
1726 unsigned Opc = ----
1727 TFL->getStackGrowthDirection() == TargetFrameLowering::StackGrowsUp ? 0
1728 ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB; 0
1729 ----
1730 Align StackAlign = TFL->getStackAlign(); 0
1731 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, VT, SP, Size); // Value 0
1732 if (Alignment > StackAlign) 0
1733 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp1, 0
1734 DAG.getConstant(-Alignment.value(), dl, VT)); 0
1735 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, dl, SPReg, Tmp1); // Output chain 0
1736 ----
1737 Tmp2 = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, 0, 0, SDValue(), dl); 0
1738 ----
1739 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
1740 Results.push_back(Tmp2); 0
1741 } 0
1742 ----
1743 /// Emit a store/load combination to the stack. This stores ----
1744 /// SrcOp to a stack slot of type SlotVT, truncating it if needed. It then does ----
1745 /// a load from the stack slot to DestVT, extending it if needed. ----
1746 /// The resultant code need not be legal. ----
1747 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::EmitStackConvert(SDValue SrcOp, EVT SlotVT, 0
1748 EVT DestVT, const SDLoc &dl) { ----
1749 return EmitStackConvert(SrcOp, SlotVT, DestVT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode()); 0
1750 } ----
1751 ----
1752 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::EmitStackConvert(SDValue SrcOp, EVT SlotVT, 0
1753 EVT DestVT, const SDLoc &dl, ----
1754 SDValue Chain) { ----
1755 EVT SrcVT = SrcOp.getValueType(); 0
1756 Type *DestType = DestVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0
1757 Align DestAlign = DAG.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(DestType); 0
1758 ----
1759 // Don't convert with stack if the load/store is expensive. ----
1760 if ((SrcVT.bitsGT(SlotVT) && 0
1761 !TLI.isTruncStoreLegalOrCustom(SrcOp.getValueType(), SlotVT)) || 0
1762 (SlotVT.bitsLT(DestVT) && 0
1763 !TLI.isLoadExtLegalOrCustom(ISD::EXTLOAD, DestVT, SlotVT))) 0
1764 return SDValue(); 0
1765 ----
1766 // Create the stack frame object. ----
1767 Align SrcAlign = DAG.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign( 0
1768 SrcOp.getValueType().getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext())); 0
1769 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(SlotVT.getStoreSize(), SrcAlign); 0
1770 ----
1771 FrameIndexSDNode *StackPtrFI = cast(FIPtr); 0
1772 int SPFI = StackPtrFI->getIndex(); 0
1773 MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo = ----
1774 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI); 0
1775 ----
1776 // Emit a store to the stack slot. Use a truncstore if the input value is ----
1777 // later than DestVT. ----
1778 SDValue Store; 0
1779 ----
1780 if (SrcVT.bitsGT(SlotVT)) 0
1781 Store = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, SrcOp, FIPtr, PtrInfo, 0
1782 SlotVT, SrcAlign); ----
1783 else { ----
1784 assert(SrcVT.bitsEq(SlotVT) && "Invalid store"); 0
1785 Store = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, SrcOp, FIPtr, PtrInfo, SrcAlign); 0
1786 } ----
1787 ----
1788 // Result is a load from the stack slot. ----
1789 if (SlotVT.bitsEq(DestVT)) 0
1790 return DAG.getLoad(DestVT, dl, Store, FIPtr, PtrInfo, DestAlign); 0
1791 ----
1792 assert(SlotVT.bitsLT(DestVT) && "Unknown extension!"); 0
1793 return DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, DestVT, Store, FIPtr, PtrInfo, SlotVT, 0
1794 DestAlign); 0
1795 } ----
1796 ----
1797 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandSCALAR_TO_VECTOR(SDNode *Node) { 0
1798 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
1799 // Create a vector sized/aligned stack slot, store the value to element #0, ----
1800 // then load the whole vector back out. ----
1801 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(Node->getValueType(0)); 0
1802 ----
1803 FrameIndexSDNode *StackPtrFI = cast(StackPtr); 0
1804 int SPFI = StackPtrFI->getIndex(); 0
1805 ----
1806 SDValue Ch = DAG.getTruncStore( 0
1807 DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Node->getOperand(0), StackPtr, 0
1808 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI), 0
1809 Node->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType()); 0
1810 return DAG.getLoad( 0
1811 Node->getValueType(0), dl, Ch, StackPtr, ----
1812 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI)); 0
1813 } 0
1814 ----
1815 static bool ----
1816 ExpandBVWithShuffles(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG, 0
1817 const TargetLowering &TLI, SDValue &Res) { ----
1818 unsigned NumElems = Node->getNumOperands(); 0
1819 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
1820 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1821 ----
1822 // Try to group the scalars into pairs, shuffle the pairs together, then ----
1823 // shuffle the pairs of pairs together, etc. until the vector has ----
1824 // been built. This will work only if all of the necessary shuffle masks ----
1825 // are legal. ----
1826 ----
1827 // We do this in two phases; first to check the legality of the shuffles, ----
1828 // and next, assuming that all shuffles are legal, to create the new nodes. ----
1829 for (int Phase = 0; Phase < 2; ++Phase) { 0
1830 SmallVector>, 16> IntermedVals, 0
1831 NewIntermedVals; 0
1832 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElems; ++i) { 0
1833 SDValue V = Node->getOperand(i); 0
1834 if (V.isUndef()) 0
1835 continue; 0
1836 ----
1837 SDValue Vec; 0
1838 if (Phase) 0
1839 Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, VT, V); 0
1840 IntermedVals.push_back(std::make_pair(Vec, SmallVector(1, i))); 0
1841 } ----
1842 ----
1843 while (IntermedVals.size() > 2) { 0
1844 NewIntermedVals.clear(); 0
1845 for (unsigned i = 0, e = (IntermedVals.size() & ~1u); i < e; i += 2) { 0
1846 // This vector and the next vector are shuffled together (simply to ----
1847 // append the one to the other). ----
1848 SmallVector ShuffleVec(NumElems, -1); 0
1849 ----
1850 SmallVector FinalIndices; 0
1851 FinalIndices.reserve(IntermedVals[i].second.size() + 0
1852 IntermedVals[i+1].second.size()); 0
1853 ----
1854 int k = 0; 0
1855 for (unsigned j = 0, f = IntermedVals[i].second.size(); j != f; 0
1856 ++j, ++k) { 0
1857 ShuffleVec[k] = j; 0
1858 FinalIndices.push_back(IntermedVals[i].second[j]); 0
1859 } ----
1860 for (unsigned j = 0, f = IntermedVals[i+1].second.size(); j != f; 0
1861 ++j, ++k) { 0
1862 ShuffleVec[k] = NumElems + j; 0
1863 FinalIndices.push_back(IntermedVals[i+1].second[j]); 0
1864 } ----
1865 ----
1866 SDValue Shuffle; 0
1867 if (Phase) 0
1868 Shuffle = DAG.getVectorShuffle(VT, dl, IntermedVals[i].first, 0
1869 IntermedVals[i+1].first, 0
1870 ShuffleVec); ----
1871 else if (!TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(ShuffleVec, VT)) 0
1872 return false; 0
1873 NewIntermedVals.push_back( 0
1874 std::make_pair(Shuffle, std::move(FinalIndices))); 0
1875 } 0
1876 ----
1877 // If we had an odd number of defined values, then append the last ----
1878 // element to the array of new vectors. ----
1879 if ((IntermedVals.size() & 1) != 0) 0
1880 NewIntermedVals.push_back(IntermedVals.back()); 0
1881 ----
1882 IntermedVals.swap(NewIntermedVals); 0
1883 } ----
1884 ----
1885 assert(IntermedVals.size() <= 2 && IntermedVals.size() > 0 && 0
1886 "Invalid number of intermediate vectors"); ----
1887 SDValue Vec1 = IntermedVals[0].first; 0
1888 SDValue Vec2; 0
1889 if (IntermedVals.size() > 1) 0
1890 Vec2 = IntermedVals[1].first; 0
1891 else if (Phase) 0
1892 Vec2 = DAG.getUNDEF(VT); 0
1893 ----
1894 SmallVector ShuffleVec(NumElems, -1); 0
1895 for (unsigned i = 0, e = IntermedVals[0].second.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
1896 ShuffleVec[IntermedVals[0].second[i]] = i; 0
1897 for (unsigned i = 0, e = IntermedVals[1].second.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
1898 ShuffleVec[IntermedVals[1].second[i]] = NumElems + i; 0
1899 ----
1900 if (Phase) 0
1901 Res = DAG.getVectorShuffle(VT, dl, Vec1, Vec2, ShuffleVec); 0
1902 else if (!TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(ShuffleVec, VT)) 0
1903 return false; 0
1904 } 0
1905 ----
1906 return true; 0
1907 } 0
1908 ----
1909 /// Expand a BUILD_VECTOR node on targets that don't ----
1910 /// support the operation, but do support the resultant vector type. ----
1911 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandBUILD_VECTOR(SDNode *Node) { 0
1912 unsigned NumElems = Node->getNumOperands(); 0
1913 SDValue Value1, Value2; 0
1914 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
1915 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
1916 EVT OpVT = Node->getOperand(0).getValueType(); 0
1917 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType(); 0
1918 ----
1919 // If the only non-undef value is the low element, turn this into a ----
1920 // SCALAR_TO_VECTOR node. If this is { X, X, X, X }, determine X. ----
1921 bool isOnlyLowElement = true; 0
1922 bool MoreThanTwoValues = false; 0
1923 bool isConstant = true; 0
1924 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElems; ++i) { 0
1925 SDValue V = Node->getOperand(i); 0
1926 if (V.isUndef()) 0
1927 continue; 0
1928 if (i > 0) 0
1929 isOnlyLowElement = false; 0
1930 if (!isa(V) && !isa(V)) 0
1931 isConstant = false; 0
1932 ----
1933 if (!Value1.getNode()) { 0
1934 Value1 = V; 0
1935 } else if (!Value2.getNode()) { 0
1936 if (V != Value1) 0
1937 Value2 = V; 0
1938 } else if (V != Value1 && V != Value2) { 0
1939 MoreThanTwoValues = true; 0
1940 } ----
1941 } ----
1942 ----
1943 if (!Value1.getNode()) 0
1944 return DAG.getUNDEF(VT); 0
1945 ----
1946 if (isOnlyLowElement) 0
1947 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, VT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
1948 ----
1949 // If all elements are constants, create a load from the constant pool. ----
1950 if (isConstant) { 0
1951 SmallVector CV; 0
1952 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumElems; i != e; ++i) { 0
1953 if (ConstantFPSDNode *V = 0
1954 dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(i))) { 0
1955 CV.push_back(const_cast(V->getConstantFPValue())); 0
1956 } else if (ConstantSDNode *V = 0
1957 dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(i))) { 0
1958 if (OpVT==EltVT) 0
1959 CV.push_back(const_cast(V->getConstantIntValue())); 0
1960 else { ----
1961 // If OpVT and EltVT don't match, EltVT is not legal and the ----
1962 // element values have been promoted/truncated earlier. Undo this; ----
1963 // we don't want a v16i8 to become a v16i32 for example. ----
1964 const ConstantInt *CI = V->getConstantIntValue(); 0
1965 CV.push_back(ConstantInt::get(EltVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()), 0
1966 CI->getZExtValue())); ----
1967 } ----
1968 } else { ----
1969 assert(Node->getOperand(i).isUndef()); 0
1970 Type *OpNTy = EltVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0
1971 CV.push_back(UndefValue::get(OpNTy)); 0
1972 } ----
1973 } ----
1974 Constant *CP = ConstantVector::get(CV); 0
1975 SDValue CPIdx = ----
1976 DAG.getConstantPool(CP, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
1977 Align Alignment = cast(CPIdx)->getAlign(); 0
1978 return DAG.getLoad( 0
1979 VT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx, 0
1980 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), 0
1981 Alignment); 0
1982 } 0
1983 ----
1984 SmallSet DefinedValues; 0
1985 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElems; ++i) { 0
1986 if (Node->getOperand(i).isUndef()) 0
1987 continue; 0
1988 DefinedValues.insert(Node->getOperand(i)); 0
1989 } ----
1990 ----
1991 if (TLI.shouldExpandBuildVectorWithShuffles(VT, DefinedValues.size())) { 0
1992 if (!MoreThanTwoValues) { 0
1993 SmallVector ShuffleVec(NumElems, -1); 0
1994 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElems; ++i) { 0
1995 SDValue V = Node->getOperand(i); 0
1996 if (V.isUndef()) 0
1997 continue; 0
1998 ShuffleVec[i] = V == Value1 ? 0 : NumElems; 0
1999 } ----
2000 if (TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(ShuffleVec, Node->getValueType(0))) { 0
2001 // Get the splatted value into the low element of a vector register. ----
2002 SDValue Vec1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, VT, Value1); 0
2003 SDValue Vec2; 0
2004 if (Value2.getNode()) 0
2005 Vec2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, VT, Value2); 0
2006 else ----
2007 Vec2 = DAG.getUNDEF(VT); 0
2008 ----
2009 // Return shuffle(LowValVec, undef, <0,0,0,0>) ----
2010 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(VT, dl, Vec1, Vec2, ShuffleVec); 0
2011 } ----
2012 } else { 0
2013 SDValue Res; 0
2014 if (ExpandBVWithShuffles(Node, DAG, TLI, Res)) 0
2015 return Res; 0
2016 } ----
2017 } ----
2018 ----
2019 // Otherwise, we can't handle this case efficiently. ----
2020 return ExpandVectorBuildThroughStack(Node); 0
2021 } 0
2022 ----
2023 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandSPLAT_VECTOR(SDNode *Node) { 0
2024 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
2025 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2026 SDValue SplatVal = Node->getOperand(0); 0
2027 ----
2028 return DAG.getSplatBuildVector(VT, DL, SplatVal); 0
2029 } 0
2030 ----
2031 // Expand a node into a call to a libcall, returning the value as the first ----
2032 // result and the chain as the second. If the result value does not fit into a ----
2033 // register, return the lo part and set the hi part to the by-reg argument in ----
2034 // the first. If it does fit into a single register, return the result and ----
2035 // leave the Hi part unset. ----
2036 std::pair SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandLibCall(RTLIB::Libcall LC, SDNode *Node, 0
2037 TargetLowering::ArgListTy &&Args, ----
2038 bool isSigned) { ----
2039 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalSymbol(TLI.getLibcallName(LC), 0
2040 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
2041 ----
2042 EVT RetVT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2043 Type *RetTy = RetVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0
2044 ----
2045 // By default, the input chain to this libcall is the entry node of the ----
2046 // function. If the libcall is going to be emitted as a tail call then ----
2047 // TLI.isUsedByReturnOnly will change it to the right chain if the return ----
2048 // node which is being folded has a non-entry input chain. ----
2049 SDValue InChain = DAG.getEntryNode(); 0
2050 ----
2051 // isTailCall may be true since the callee does not reference caller stack ----
2052 // frame. Check if it's in the right position and that the return types match. ----
2053 SDValue TCChain = InChain; 0
2054 const Function &F = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction(); 0
2055 bool isTailCall = ----
2056 TLI.isInTailCallPosition(DAG, Node, TCChain) && 0
2057 (RetTy == F.getReturnType() || F.getReturnType()->isVoidTy()); 0
2058 if (isTailCall) 0
2059 InChain = TCChain; 0
2060 ----
2061 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG); 0
2062 bool signExtend = TLI.shouldSignExtendTypeInLibCall(RetVT, isSigned); 0
2063 CLI.setDebugLoc(SDLoc(Node)) 0
2064 .setChain(InChain) 0
2065 .setLibCallee(TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(LC), RetTy, Callee, 0
2066 std::move(Args)) 0
2067 .setTailCall(isTailCall) 0
2068 .setSExtResult(signExtend) 0
2069 .setZExtResult(!signExtend) 0
2070 .setIsPostTypeLegalization(true); 0
2071 ----
2072 std::pair CallInfo = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI); 0
2073 ----
2074 if (!CallInfo.second.getNode()) { 0
2075 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Created tailcall: "; DAG.getRoot().dump(&DAG)); 0
2076 // It's a tailcall, return the chain (which is the DAG root). ----
2077 return {DAG.getRoot(), DAG.getRoot()}; 0
2078 } ----
2079 ----
2080 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Created libcall: "; CallInfo.first.dump(&DAG)); 0
2081 return CallInfo; 0
2082 } 0
2083 ----
2084 std::pair SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandLibCall(RTLIB::Libcall LC, SDNode *Node, 0
2085 bool isSigned) { ----
2086 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args; 0
2087 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry; 0
2088 for (const SDValue &Op : Node->op_values()) { 0
2089 EVT ArgVT = Op.getValueType(); 0
2090 Type *ArgTy = ArgVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0
2091 Entry.Node = Op; 0
2092 Entry.Ty = ArgTy; 0
2093 Entry.IsSExt = TLI.shouldSignExtendTypeInLibCall(ArgVT, isSigned); 0
2094 Entry.IsZExt = !Entry.IsSExt; 0
2095 Args.push_back(Entry); 0
2096 } ----
2097 ----
2098 return ExpandLibCall(LC, Node, std::move(Args), isSigned); 0
2099 } 0

2101 void SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandFrexpLibCall( 0
2102 SDNode *Node, SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
2103 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
2104 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2105 EVT ExpVT = Node->getValueType(1); 0
2106 ----
2107 SDValue FPOp = Node->getOperand(0); 0
2108 ----

2110 Type *ArgTy = ArgVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0

2128 ----
2129 int FrameIdx = cast(StackSlot)->getIndex(); 0

2131 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FrameIdx); 0
2132 ----

2137 ----
2138 Results.push_back(Call); 0
