2213 /// Issue libcalls to __{u}divmod to compute div / rem pairs. ----
2214 void ----
2215 SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandDivRemLibCall(SDNode *Node, 0
2216 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
2217 unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode(); 0
2218 bool isSigned = Opcode == ISD::SDIVREM; 0
2219 ----
2220 RTLIB::Libcall LC; ----
2221 switch (Node->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) { 0
2222 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected request for libcall!"); 0
2223 case MVT::i8: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I8 : RTLIB::UDIVREM_I8; break; 0
2224 case MVT::i16: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I16 : RTLIB::UDIVREM_I16; break; 0
2225 case MVT::i32: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I32 : RTLIB::UDIVREM_I32; break; 0
2226 case MVT::i64: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I64 : RTLIB::UDIVREM_I64; break; 0
2227 case MVT::i128: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I128:RTLIB::UDIVREM_I128; break; 0
2228 } ----
2229 ----
2230 // The input chain to this libcall is the entry node of the function. ----
2231 // Legalizing the call will automatically add the previous call to the ----
2232 // dependence. ----
2233 SDValue InChain = DAG.getEntryNode(); 0
2234 ----
2235 EVT RetVT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2236 Type *RetTy = RetVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0
2237 ----
2238 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args; 0
2239 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry; 0
2240 for (const SDValue &Op : Node->op_values()) { 0
2241 EVT ArgVT = Op.getValueType(); 0
2242 Type *ArgTy = ArgVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0
2243 Entry.Node = Op; 0
2244 Entry.Ty = ArgTy; 0
2245 Entry.IsSExt = isSigned; 0
2246 Entry.IsZExt = !isSigned; 0
2247 Args.push_back(Entry); 0
2248 } ----
2249 ----
2250 // Also pass the return address of the remainder. ----
2251 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(RetVT); 0
2252 Entry.Node = FIPtr; 0
2253 Entry.Ty = RetTy->getPointerTo(); 0
2254 Entry.IsSExt = isSigned; 0
2255 Entry.IsZExt = !isSigned; 0
2256 Args.push_back(Entry); 0
2257 ----
2258 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalSymbol(TLI.getLibcallName(LC), 0
2259 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
2260 ----
2261 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
2262 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG); 0
2263 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl) 0
2264 .setChain(InChain) 0
2265 .setLibCallee(TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(LC), RetTy, Callee, 0
2266 std::move(Args)) 0
2267 .setSExtResult(isSigned) 0
2268 .setZExtResult(!isSigned); 0
2269 ----
2270 std::pair CallInfo = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI); 0
2271 ----
2272 // Remainder is loaded back from the stack frame. ----
2273 SDValue Rem = ----
2274 DAG.getLoad(RetVT, dl, CallInfo.second, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo()); 0
2275 Results.push_back(CallInfo.first); 0
2276 Results.push_back(Rem); 0
2277 } 0
2278 ----
2279 /// Return true if sincos libcall is available. ----
2280 static bool isSinCosLibcallAvailable(SDNode *Node, const TargetLowering &TLI) { 0
2281 RTLIB::Libcall LC; ----
2282 switch (Node->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) { 0
2283 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected request for libcall!"); 0
2284 case MVT::f32: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F32; break; 0
2285 case MVT::f64: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F64; break; 0
2286 case MVT::f80: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F80; break; 0
2287 case MVT::f128: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F128; break; 0
2288 case MVT::ppcf128: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_PPCF128; break; 0
2289 } ----
2290 return TLI.getLibcallName(LC) != nullptr; 0
2291 } ----
2292 ----
2293 /// Only issue sincos libcall if both sin and cos are needed. ----
2294 static bool useSinCos(SDNode *Node) { 0
2295 unsigned OtherOpcode = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FSIN 0
2296 ? ISD::FCOS : ISD::FSIN; 0
2297 ----
2298 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
2299 for (const SDNode *User : Op0.getNode()->uses()) { 0
2300 if (User == Node) 0
2301 continue; 0
2302 // The other user might have been turned into sincos already. ----
2303 if (User->getOpcode() == OtherOpcode || User->getOpcode() == ISD::FSINCOS) 0
2304 return true; 0
2305 } ----
2306 return false; 0
2307 } ----
2308 ----
2309 /// Issue libcalls to sincos to compute sin / cos pairs. ----
2310 void ----
2311 SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandSinCosLibCall(SDNode *Node, 0
2312 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
2313 RTLIB::Libcall LC; ----
2314 switch (Node->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) { 0
2315 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected request for libcall!"); 0
2316 case MVT::f32: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F32; break; 0
2317 case MVT::f64: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F64; break; 0
2318 case MVT::f80: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F80; break; 0
2319 case MVT::f128: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F128; break; 0
2320 case MVT::ppcf128: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_PPCF128; break; 0
2321 } ----
2322 ----
2323 // The input chain to this libcall is the entry node of the function. ----
2324 // Legalizing the call will automatically add the previous call to the ----
2325 // dependence. ----
2326 SDValue InChain = DAG.getEntryNode(); 0
2327 ----
2328 EVT RetVT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2329 Type *RetTy = RetVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()); 0
2330 ----
2331 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args; 0
2332 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry; 0
2333 ----
2334 // Pass the argument. ----
2335 Entry.Node = Node->getOperand(0); 0
2336 Entry.Ty = RetTy; 0
2337 Entry.IsSExt = false; 0
2338 Entry.IsZExt = false; 0
2339 Args.push_back(Entry); 0
2340 ----
2341 // Pass the return address of sin. ----
2342 SDValue SinPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(RetVT); 0
2343 Entry.Node = SinPtr; 0
2344 Entry.Ty = RetTy->getPointerTo(); 0
2345 Entry.IsSExt = false; 0
2346 Entry.IsZExt = false; 0
2347 Args.push_back(Entry); 0
2348 ----
2349 // Also pass the return address of the cos. ----
2350 SDValue CosPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(RetVT); 0
2351 Entry.Node = CosPtr; 0
2352 Entry.Ty = RetTy->getPointerTo(); 0
2353 Entry.IsSExt = false; 0
2354 Entry.IsZExt = false; 0
2355 Args.push_back(Entry); 0
2356 ----
2357 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalSymbol(TLI.getLibcallName(LC), 0
2358 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
2359 ----
2360 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
2361 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG); 0
2362 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl).setChain(InChain).setLibCallee( 0
2363 TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(LC), Type::getVoidTy(*DAG.getContext()), Callee, 0
2364 std::move(Args)); 0
2365 ----
2366 std::pair CallInfo = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI); 0
2367 ----
2368 Results.push_back( 0
2369 DAG.getLoad(RetVT, dl, CallInfo.second, SinPtr, MachinePointerInfo())); 0
2370 Results.push_back( 0
2371 DAG.getLoad(RetVT, dl, CallInfo.second, CosPtr, MachinePointerInfo())); 0
2372 } 0
2373 ----
2374 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::expandLdexp(SDNode *Node) const { 0
2375 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
2376 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2377 SDValue X = Node->getOperand(0); 0
2378 SDValue N = Node->getOperand(1); 0
2379 EVT ExpVT = N.getValueType(); 0
2380 EVT AsIntVT = VT.changeTypeToInteger(); 0
2381 if (AsIntVT == EVT()) // TODO: How to handle f80? 0
2382 return SDValue(); 0
2383 ----
2384 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FLDEXP) // TODO 0
2385 return SDValue(); 0
2386 ----
2387 SDNodeFlags NSW; 0
2388 NSW.setNoSignedWrap(true); 0
2389 SDNodeFlags NUW_NSW; 0
2390 NUW_NSW.setNoUnsignedWrap(true); 0
2391 NUW_NSW.setNoSignedWrap(true); 0
2392 ----
2393 EVT SetCCVT = ----
2394 TLI.getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), ExpVT); 0
2395 const fltSemantics &FltSem = SelectionDAG::EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT); 0
2396 ----
2397 const APFloat::ExponentType MaxExpVal = APFloat::semanticsMaxExponent(FltSem); 0
2398 const APFloat::ExponentType MinExpVal = APFloat::semanticsMinExponent(FltSem); 0
2399 const int Precision = APFloat::semanticsPrecision(FltSem); 0
2400 ----
2401 const SDValue MaxExp = DAG.getConstant(MaxExpVal, dl, ExpVT); 0
2402 const SDValue MinExp = DAG.getConstant(MinExpVal, dl, ExpVT); 0
2403 ----
2404 const SDValue DoubleMaxExp = DAG.getConstant(2 * MaxExpVal, dl, ExpVT); 0
2405 ----
2406 const APFloat One(FltSem, "1.0"); 0
2407 APFloat ScaleUpK = scalbn(One, MaxExpVal, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven); 0
2408 ----
2409 // Offset by precision to avoid denormal range. ----
2410 APFloat ScaleDownK = ----
2411 scalbn(One, MinExpVal + Precision, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven); 0
2412 ----
2413 // TODO: Should really introduce control flow and use a block for the > ----
2414 // MaxExp, < MinExp cases ----
2415 ----
2416 // First, handle exponents Exp > MaxExp and scale down. ----
2417 SDValue NGtMaxExp = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, N, MaxExp, ISD::SETGT); 0
2418 ----
2419 SDValue DecN0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, ExpVT, N, MaxExp, NSW); 0
2420 SDValue ClampMaxVal = DAG.getConstant(3 * MaxExpVal, dl, ExpVT); 0
2421 SDValue ClampN_Big = DAG.getNode(ISD::SMIN, dl, ExpVT, N, ClampMaxVal); 0
2422 SDValue DecN1 = ----
2423 DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, ExpVT, ClampN_Big, DoubleMaxExp, NSW); 0
2424 ----
2425 SDValue ScaleUpTwice = ----
2426 DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, N, DoubleMaxExp, ISD::SETUGT); 0
2427 ----
2428 const SDValue ScaleUpVal = DAG.getConstantFP(ScaleUpK, dl, VT); 0
2429 SDValue ScaleUp0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, dl, VT, X, ScaleUpVal); 0
2430 SDValue ScaleUp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, dl, VT, ScaleUp0, ScaleUpVal); 0
2431 ----
2432 SDValue SelectN_Big = ----
2433 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, ExpVT, ScaleUpTwice, DecN1, DecN0); 0
2434 SDValue SelectX_Big = ----
2435 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, ScaleUpTwice, ScaleUp1, ScaleUp0); 0
2436 ----
2437 // Now handle exponents Exp < MinExp ----
2438 SDValue NLtMinExp = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, N, MinExp, ISD::SETLT); 0
2439 ----
2440 SDValue Increment0 = DAG.getConstant(-(MinExpVal + Precision), dl, ExpVT); 0
2441 SDValue Increment1 = DAG.getConstant(-2 * (MinExpVal + Precision), dl, ExpVT); 0
2442 ----
2443 SDValue IncN0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, ExpVT, N, Increment0, NUW_NSW); 0
2444 ----
2445 SDValue ClampMinVal = ----
2446 DAG.getConstant(3 * MinExpVal + 2 * Precision, dl, ExpVT); 0
2447 SDValue ClampN_Small = DAG.getNode(ISD::SMAX, dl, ExpVT, N, ClampMinVal); 0
2448 SDValue IncN1 = ----
2449 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, ExpVT, ClampN_Small, Increment1, NSW); 0
2450 ----
2451 const SDValue ScaleDownVal = DAG.getConstantFP(ScaleDownK, dl, VT); 0
2452 SDValue ScaleDown0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, dl, VT, X, ScaleDownVal); 0
2453 SDValue ScaleDown1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, dl, VT, ScaleDown0, ScaleDownVal); 0
2454 ----
2455 SDValue ScaleDownTwice = DAG.getSetCC( 0
2456 dl, SetCCVT, N, DAG.getConstant(2 * MinExpVal + Precision, dl, ExpVT), 0
2457 ISD::SETULT); ----
2458 ----
2459 SDValue SelectN_Small = ----
2460 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, ExpVT, ScaleDownTwice, IncN1, IncN0); 0
2461 SDValue SelectX_Small = ----
2462 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, ScaleDownTwice, ScaleDown1, ScaleDown0); 0
2463 ----
2464 // Now combine the two out of range exponent handling cases with the base ----
2465 // case. ----
2466 SDValue NewX = DAG.getNode( 0
2467 ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, NGtMaxExp, SelectX_Big, ----
2468 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, NLtMinExp, SelectX_Small, X)); 0
2469 ----
2470 SDValue NewN = DAG.getNode( 0
2471 ISD::SELECT, dl, ExpVT, NGtMaxExp, SelectN_Big, ----
2472 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, ExpVT, NLtMinExp, SelectN_Small, N)); 0
2473 ----
2474 SDValue BiasedN = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, ExpVT, NewN, MaxExp, NSW); 0
2475 ----
2476 SDValue ExponentShiftAmt = ----
2477 DAG.getShiftAmountConstant(Precision - 1, ExpVT, dl); 0
2478 SDValue CastExpToValTy = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(BiasedN, dl, AsIntVT); 0
2479 ----
2480 SDValue AsInt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, AsIntVT, CastExpToValTy, 0
2481 ExponentShiftAmt, NUW_NSW); ----
2482 SDValue AsFP = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VT, AsInt); 0
2483 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, dl, VT, NewX, AsFP); 0
2484 } 0
2485 ----
2486 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::expandFrexp(SDNode *Node) const { 0
2487 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
2488 SDValue Val = Node->getOperand(0); 0
2489 EVT VT = Val.getValueType(); 0
2490 EVT ExpVT = Node->getValueType(1); 0
2491 EVT AsIntVT = VT.changeTypeToInteger(); 0
2492 if (AsIntVT == EVT()) // TODO: How to handle f80? 0
2493 return SDValue(); 0
2494 ----
2495 const fltSemantics &FltSem = SelectionDAG::EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT); 0
2496 const APFloat::ExponentType MinExpVal = APFloat::semanticsMinExponent(FltSem); 0
2497 const unsigned Precision = APFloat::semanticsPrecision(FltSem); 0
2498 const unsigned BitSize = VT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
2499 ----
2500 // TODO: Could introduce control flow and skip over the denormal handling. ----
2501 ----
2502 // scale_up = fmul value, scalbn(1.0, precision + 1) ----
2503 // extracted_exp = (bitcast value to uint) >> precision - 1 ----
2504 // biased_exp = extracted_exp + min_exp ----
2505 // extracted_fract = (bitcast value to uint) & (fract_mask | sign_mask) ----
2506 // ----
2507 // is_denormal = val < smallest_normalized ----
2508 // computed_fract = is_denormal ? scale_up : extracted_fract ----
2509 // computed_exp = is_denormal ? biased_exp + (-precision - 1) : biased_exp ----
2510 // ----
2511 // result_0 = (!isfinite(val) || iszero(val)) ? val : computed_fract ----
2512 // result_1 = (!isfinite(val) || iszero(val)) ? 0 : computed_exp ----
2513 ----
2514 SDValue NegSmallestNormalizedInt = DAG.getConstant( 0
2515 APFloat::getSmallestNormalized(FltSem, true).bitcastToAPInt(), dl, 0
2516 AsIntVT); ----
2517 ----
2518 SDValue SmallestNormalizedInt = DAG.getConstant( 0
2519 APFloat::getSmallestNormalized(FltSem, false).bitcastToAPInt(), dl, 0
2520 AsIntVT); ----
2521 ----
2522 // Masks out the exponent bits. ----
2523 SDValue ExpMask = ----
2524 DAG.getConstant(APFloat::getInf(FltSem).bitcastToAPInt(), dl, AsIntVT); 0
2525 ----
2526 // Mask out the exponent part of the value. ----
2527 // ----
2528 // e.g, for f32 FractSignMaskVal = 0x807fffff ----
2529 APInt FractSignMaskVal = APInt::getBitsSet(BitSize, 0, Precision - 1); 0
2530 FractSignMaskVal.setBit(BitSize - 1); // Set the sign bit 0
2531 ----
2532 APInt SignMaskVal = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitSize); 0
2533 SDValue SignMask = DAG.getConstant(SignMaskVal, dl, AsIntVT); 0
2534 ----
2535 SDValue FractSignMask = DAG.getConstant(FractSignMaskVal, dl, AsIntVT); 0
2536 ----
2537 const APFloat One(FltSem, "1.0"); 0
2538 // Scale a possible denormal input. ----
2539 // e.g., for f64, 0x1p+54 ----
2540 APFloat ScaleUpKVal = ----
2541 scalbn(One, Precision + 1, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven); 0
2542 ----
2543 SDValue ScaleUpK = DAG.getConstantFP(ScaleUpKVal, dl, VT); 0
2544 SDValue ScaleUp = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, dl, VT, Val, ScaleUpK); 0
2545 ----
2546 EVT SetCCVT = ----
2547 TLI.getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT); 0
2548 ----
2549 SDValue AsInt = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, AsIntVT, Val); 0
2550 ----
2551 SDValue Abs = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, AsIntVT, AsInt, SignMask); 0
2552 ----
2553 SDValue AddNegSmallestNormal = ----
2554 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, AsIntVT, Abs, NegSmallestNormalizedInt); 0
2555 SDValue DenormOrZero = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, AddNegSmallestNormal, 0
2556 NegSmallestNormalizedInt, ISD::SETULE); ----
2557 ----
2558 SDValue IsDenormal = ----
2559 DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCVT, Abs, SmallestNormalizedInt, ISD::SETULT); 0
2560 ----
2561 SDValue MinExp = DAG.getConstant(MinExpVal, dl, ExpVT); 0
2562 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, ExpVT); 0
2563 ----
2564 SDValue ScaledAsInt = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, AsIntVT, ScaleUp); 0
2565 SDValue ScaledSelect = ----
2566 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, AsIntVT, IsDenormal, ScaledAsInt, AsInt); 0
2567 ----
2568 SDValue ExpMaskScaled = ----
2569 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, AsIntVT, ScaledAsInt, ExpMask); 0
2570 ----
2571 SDValue ScaledValue = ----
2572 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, AsIntVT, IsDenormal, ExpMaskScaled, Abs); 0
2573 ----
2574 // Extract the exponent bits. ----
2575 SDValue ExponentShiftAmt = ----
2576 DAG.getShiftAmountConstant(Precision - 1, AsIntVT, dl); 0
2577 SDValue ShiftedExp = ----
2578 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, AsIntVT, ScaledValue, ExponentShiftAmt); 0
2579 SDValue Exp = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(ShiftedExp, dl, ExpVT); 0
2580 ----
2581 SDValue NormalBiasedExp = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, ExpVT, Exp, MinExp); 0
2582 SDValue DenormalOffset = DAG.getConstant(-Precision - 1, dl, ExpVT); 0
2583 SDValue DenormalExpBias = ----
2584 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, ExpVT, IsDenormal, DenormalOffset, Zero); 0
2585 ----
2586 SDValue MaskedFractAsInt = ----
2587 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, AsIntVT, ScaledSelect, FractSignMask); 0
2588 const APFloat Half(FltSem, "0.5"); 0
2589 SDValue FPHalf = DAG.getConstant(Half.bitcastToAPInt(), dl, AsIntVT); 0
2590 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, AsIntVT, MaskedFractAsInt, FPHalf); 0
2591 SDValue MaskedFract = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VT, Or); 0
2592 ----
2593 SDValue ComputedExp = ----
2594 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, ExpVT, NormalBiasedExp, DenormalExpBias); 0
2595 ----
2596 SDValue Result0 = ----
2597 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, VT, DenormOrZero, Val, MaskedFract); 0
2598 ----
2599 SDValue Result1 = ----
2600 DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, ExpVT, DenormOrZero, Zero, ComputedExp); 0
2601 ----
2602 return DAG.getMergeValues({Result0, Result1}, dl); 0
2603 } 0
2604 ----
2605 /// This function is responsible for legalizing a ----
2606 /// INT_TO_FP operation of the specified operand when the target requests that ----
2607 /// we expand it. At this point, we know that the result and operand types are ----
2608 /// legal for the target. ----
2609 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandLegalINT_TO_FP(SDNode *Node, 0
2610 SDValue &Chain) { ----
2611 bool isSigned = (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP || 0
2612 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SINT_TO_FP); 0
2613 EVT DestVT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2614 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
2615 unsigned OpNo = Node->isStrictFPOpcode() ? 1 : 0; 0
2616 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(OpNo); 0
2617 EVT SrcVT = Op0.getValueType(); 0
2618 ----
2619 // TODO: Should any fast-math-flags be set for the created nodes? ----
2620 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legalizing INT_TO_FP\n"); 0
2621 if (SrcVT == MVT::i32 && TLI.isTypeLegal(MVT::f64) && 0
2622 (DestVT.bitsLE(MVT::f64) || 0
2623 TLI.isOperationLegal(Node->isStrictFPOpcode() ? ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND 0
2624 : ISD::FP_EXTEND, ----
2625 DestVT))) { ----
2626 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "32-bit [signed|unsigned] integer to float/double " 0
2627 "expansion\n"); ----
2628 ----
2629 // Get the stack frame index of a 8 byte buffer. ----
2630 SDValue StackSlot = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(MVT::f64); 0
2631 ----
2632 SDValue Lo = Op0; 0
2633 // if signed map to unsigned space ----
2634 if (isSigned) { 0
2635 // Invert sign bit (signed to unsigned mapping). ----
2636 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, MVT::i32, Lo, 0
2637 DAG.getConstant(0x80000000u, dl, MVT::i32)); 0
2638 } ----
2639 // Initial hi portion of constructed double. ----
2640 SDValue Hi = DAG.getConstant(0x43300000u, dl, MVT::i32); 0
2641 ----
2642 // If this a big endian target, swap the lo and high data. ----
2643 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian()) 0
2644 std::swap(Lo, Hi); 0
2645 ----
2646 SDValue MemChain = DAG.getEntryNode(); 0
2647 ----
2648 // Store the lo of the constructed double. ----
2649 SDValue Store1 = DAG.getStore(MemChain, dl, Lo, StackSlot, 0
2650 MachinePointerInfo()); ----
2651 // Store the hi of the constructed double. ----
2652 SDValue HiPtr = DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(StackSlot, TypeSize::Fixed(4), dl); 0
2653 SDValue Store2 = ----
2654 DAG.getStore(MemChain, dl, Hi, HiPtr, MachinePointerInfo()); 0
2655 MemChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Store1, Store2); 0
2656 ----
2657 // load the constructed double ----
2658 SDValue Load = ----
2659 DAG.getLoad(MVT::f64, dl, MemChain, StackSlot, MachinePointerInfo()); 0
2660 // FP constant to bias correct the final result ----
2661 SDValue Bias = DAG.getConstantFP( 0
2662 isSigned ? llvm::bit_cast(0x4330000080000000ULL) 0
2663 : llvm::bit_cast(0x4330000000000000ULL), 0
2664 dl, MVT::f64); ----
2665 // Subtract the bias and get the final result. ----
2666 SDValue Sub; 0
2667 SDValue Result; 0
2668 if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) { 0
2669 Sub = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FSUB, dl, {MVT::f64, MVT::Other}, 0
2670 {Node->getOperand(0), Load, Bias}); 0
2671 Chain = Sub.getValue(1); 0
2672 if (DestVT != Sub.getValueType()) { 0
2673 std::pair ResultPair; 0
2674 ResultPair = ----
2675 DAG.getStrictFPExtendOrRound(Sub, Chain, dl, DestVT); 0
2676 Result = ResultPair.first; 0
2677 Chain = ResultPair.second; 0
2678 } ----
2679 else ----
2680 Result = Sub; 0
2681 } else { ----
2682 Sub = DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, dl, MVT::f64, Load, Bias); 0
2683 Result = DAG.getFPExtendOrRound(Sub, dl, DestVT); 0
2684 } ----
2685 return Result; 0
2686 } ----
2687 ----
2688 if (isSigned) 0
2689 return SDValue(); 0
2690 ----
2691 // TODO: Generalize this for use with other types. ----
2692 if (((SrcVT == MVT::i32 || SrcVT == MVT::i64) && DestVT == MVT::f32) || 0
2693 (SrcVT == MVT::i64 && DestVT == MVT::f64)) { 0
2694 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Converting unsigned i32/i64 to f32/f64\n"); 0
2695 // For unsigned conversions, convert them to signed conversions using the ----
2696 // algorithm from the x86_64 __floatundisf in compiler_rt. That method ----
2697 // should be valid for i32->f32 as well. ----
2698 ----
2699 // More generally this transform should be valid if there are 3 more bits ----
2700 // in the integer type than the significand. Rounding uses the first bit ----
2701 // after the width of the significand and the OR of all bits after that. So ----
2702 // we need to be able to OR the shifted out bit into one of the bits that ----
2703 // participate in the OR. ----
2704 ----
2705 // TODO: This really should be implemented using a branch rather than a ----
2706 // select. We happen to get lucky and machinesink does the right ----
2707 // thing most of the time. This would be a good candidate for a ----
2708 // pseudo-op, or, even better, for whole-function isel. ----
2709 EVT SetCCVT = getSetCCResultType(SrcVT); 0
2710 ----
2711 SDValue SignBitTest = DAG.getSetCC( 0
2712 dl, SetCCVT, Op0, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, SrcVT), ISD::SETLT); 0
2713 ----
2714 EVT ShiftVT = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(SrcVT, DAG.getDataLayout()); 0
2715 SDValue ShiftConst = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, ShiftVT); 0
2716 SDValue Shr = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, SrcVT, Op0, ShiftConst); 0
2717 SDValue AndConst = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, SrcVT); 0
2718 SDValue And = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, SrcVT, Op0, AndConst); 0
2719 SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, SrcVT, And, Shr); 0
2720 ----
2721 SDValue Slow, Fast; 0
2722 if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) { 0
2723 // In strict mode, we must avoid spurious exceptions, and therefore ----
2724 // must make sure to only emit a single STRICT_SINT_TO_FP. ----
2725 SDValue InCvt = DAG.getSelect(dl, SrcVT, SignBitTest, Or, Op0); 0
2726 Fast = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP, dl, { DestVT, MVT::Other }, 0
2727 { Node->getOperand(0), InCvt }); 0
2728 Slow = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FADD, dl, { DestVT, MVT::Other }, 0
2729 { Fast.getValue(1), Fast, Fast }); 0
2730 Chain = Slow.getValue(1); 0
2731 // The STRICT_SINT_TO_FP inherits the exception mode from the ----
2732 // incoming STRICT_UINT_TO_FP node; the STRICT_FADD node can ----
2733 // never raise any exception. ----
2734 SDNodeFlags Flags; 0
2735 Flags.setNoFPExcept(Node->getFlags().hasNoFPExcept()); 0
2736 Fast->setFlags(Flags); 0
2737 Flags.setNoFPExcept(true); 0
2738 Slow->setFlags(Flags); 0
2739 } else { ----
2740 SDValue SignCvt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, dl, DestVT, Or); 0
2741 Slow = DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, dl, DestVT, SignCvt, SignCvt); 0
2742 Fast = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, dl, DestVT, Op0); 0
2743 } ----
2744 ----
2745 return DAG.getSelect(dl, DestVT, SignBitTest, Slow, Fast); 0
2746 } ----
2747 ----
2748 // Don't expand it if there isn't cheap fadd. ----
2749 if (!TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom( 0
2750 Node->isStrictFPOpcode() ? ISD::STRICT_FADD : ISD::FADD, DestVT)) 0
2751 return SDValue(); 0
2752 ----
2753 // The following optimization is valid only if every value in SrcVT (when ----
2754 // treated as signed) is representable in DestVT. Check that the mantissa ----
2755 // size of DestVT is >= than the number of bits in SrcVT -1. ----
2756 assert(APFloat::semanticsPrecision(DAG.EVTToAPFloatSemantics(DestVT)) >= 0
2757 SrcVT.getSizeInBits() - 1 && ----
2758 "Cannot perform lossless SINT_TO_FP!"); ----
2759 ----
2760 SDValue Tmp1; 0
2761 if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) { 0
2762 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP, dl, { DestVT, MVT::Other }, 0
2763 { Node->getOperand(0), Op0 }); 0
2764 } else ----
2765 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, dl, DestVT, Op0); 0
2766 ----
2767 SDValue SignSet = DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(SrcVT), Op0, 0
2768 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, SrcVT), ISD::SETLT); 0
2769 SDValue Zero = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl), 0
2770 Four = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(4, dl); 0
2771 SDValue CstOffset = DAG.getSelect(dl, Zero.getValueType(), 0
2772 SignSet, Four, Zero); ----
2773 ----
2774 // If the sign bit of the integer is set, the large number will be treated ----
2775 // as a negative number. To counteract this, the dynamic code adds an ----
2776 // offset depending on the data type. ----
2777 uint64_t FF; ----
2778 switch (SrcVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) { 0
2779 default: 0
2780 return SDValue(); 0
2781 case MVT::i8 : FF = 0x43800000ULL; break; // 2^8 (as a float) 0
2782 case MVT::i16: FF = 0x47800000ULL; break; // 2^16 (as a float) 0
2783 case MVT::i32: FF = 0x4F800000ULL; break; // 2^32 (as a float) 0
2784 case MVT::i64: FF = 0x5F800000ULL; break; // 2^64 (as a float) 0
2785 } ----
2786 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian()) 0
2787 FF <<= 32; 0
2788 Constant *FudgeFactor = ConstantInt::get( 0
2789 Type::getInt64Ty(*DAG.getContext()), FF); 0
2790 ----
2791 SDValue CPIdx = ----
2792 DAG.getConstantPool(FudgeFactor, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
2793 Align Alignment = cast(CPIdx)->getAlign(); 0
2794 CPIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, CPIdx.getValueType(), CPIdx, CstOffset); 0
2795 Alignment = commonAlignment(Alignment, 4); 0
2796 SDValue FudgeInReg; 0
2797 if (DestVT == MVT::f32) 0
2798 FudgeInReg = DAG.getLoad( 0
2799 MVT::f32, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx, 0
2800 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), 0
2801 Alignment); ----
2802 else { ----
2803 SDValue Load = DAG.getExtLoad( 0
2804 ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, DestVT, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx, 0
2805 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), MVT::f32, 0
2806 Alignment); ----
2807 HandleSDNode Handle(Load); 0
2808 LegalizeOp(Load.getNode()); 0
2809 FudgeInReg = Handle.getValue(); 0
2810 } 0
2811 ----
2812 if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) { 0
2813 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FADD, dl, { DestVT, MVT::Other }, 0
2814 { Tmp1.getValue(1), Tmp1, FudgeInReg }); 0
2815 Chain = Result.getValue(1); 0
2816 return Result; 0
2817 } ----
2818 ----
2819 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, dl, DestVT, Tmp1, FudgeInReg); 0
2820 } 0
2821 ----
2822 /// This function is responsible for legalizing a ----
2823 /// *INT_TO_FP operation of the specified operand when the target requests that ----
2824 /// we promote it. At this point, we know that the result and operand types are ----
2825 /// legal for the target, and that there is a legal UINT_TO_FP or SINT_TO_FP ----
2826 /// operation that takes a larger input. ----
2827 void SelectionDAGLegalize::PromoteLegalINT_TO_FP( 0
2828 SDNode *N, const SDLoc &dl, SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
2829 bool IsStrict = N->isStrictFPOpcode(); 0
2830 bool IsSigned = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SINT_TO_FP || 0
2831 N->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP; 0
2832 EVT DestVT = N->getValueType(0); 0
2833 SDValue LegalOp = N->getOperand(IsStrict ? 1 : 0); 0
2834 unsigned UIntOp = IsStrict ? ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP : ISD::UINT_TO_FP; 0
2835 unsigned SIntOp = IsStrict ? ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP : ISD::SINT_TO_FP; 0
2836 ----
2837 // First step, figure out the appropriate *INT_TO_FP operation to use. ----
2838 EVT NewInTy = LegalOp.getValueType(); 0
2839 ----
2840 unsigned OpToUse = 0; 0
2841 ----
2842 // Scan for the appropriate larger type to use. ----
2843 while (true) { ----
2844 NewInTy = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(NewInTy.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy+1); 0
2845 assert(NewInTy.isInteger() && "Ran out of possibilities!"); 0
2846 ----
2847 // If the target supports SINT_TO_FP of this type, use it. ----
2848 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(SIntOp, NewInTy)) { 0
2849 OpToUse = SIntOp; 0
2850 break; 0
2851 } ----
2852 if (IsSigned) 0
2853 continue; 0
2854 ----
2855 // If the target supports UINT_TO_FP of this type, use it. ----
2856 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(UIntOp, NewInTy)) { 0
2857 OpToUse = UIntOp; 0
2858 break; 0
2859 } ----
2860 ----
2861 // Otherwise, try a larger type. ----
2862 } ----
2863 ----
2864 // Okay, we found the operation and type to use. Zero extend our input to the ----
2865 // desired type then run the operation on it. ----
2866 if (IsStrict) { 0
2867 SDValue Res = ----
2868 DAG.getNode(OpToUse, dl, {DestVT, MVT::Other}, 0
2869 {N->getOperand(0), 0
2870 DAG.getNode(IsSigned ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, 0
2871 dl, NewInTy, LegalOp)}); ----
2872 Results.push_back(Res); 0
2873 Results.push_back(Res.getValue(1)); 0
2874 return; 0
2875 } ----
2876 ----
2877 Results.push_back( 0
2878 DAG.getNode(OpToUse, dl, DestVT, 0
2879 DAG.getNode(IsSigned ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, 0
2880 dl, NewInTy, LegalOp))); ----
2881 } ----
2882 ----
2883 /// This function is responsible for legalizing a ----
2884 /// FP_TO_*INT operation of the specified operand when the target requests that ----
2885 /// we promote it. At this point, we know that the result and operand types are ----
2886 /// legal for the target, and that there is a legal FP_TO_UINT or FP_TO_SINT ----
2887 /// operation that returns a larger result. ----
2888 void SelectionDAGLegalize::PromoteLegalFP_TO_INT(SDNode *N, const SDLoc &dl, 0
2889 SmallVectorImpl &Results) { ----
2890 bool IsStrict = N->isStrictFPOpcode(); 0
2891 bool IsSigned = N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT || 0
2892 N->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT; 0
2893 EVT DestVT = N->getValueType(0); 0
2894 SDValue LegalOp = N->getOperand(IsStrict ? 1 : 0); 0
2895 // First step, figure out the appropriate FP_TO*INT operation to use. ----
2896 EVT NewOutTy = DestVT; 0
2897 ----
2898 unsigned OpToUse = 0; 0
2899 ----
2900 // Scan for the appropriate larger type to use. ----
2901 while (true) { ----
2902 NewOutTy = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(NewOutTy.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy+1); 0
2903 assert(NewOutTy.isInteger() && "Ran out of possibilities!"); 0
2904 ----
2905 // A larger signed type can hold all unsigned values of the requested type, ----
2906 // so using FP_TO_SINT is valid ----
2907 OpToUse = IsStrict ? ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT : ISD::FP_TO_SINT; 0
2908 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(OpToUse, NewOutTy)) 0
2909 break; 0
2910 ----
2911 // However, if the value may be < 0.0, we *must* use some FP_TO_SINT. ----
2912 OpToUse = IsStrict ? ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT : ISD::FP_TO_UINT; 0
2913 if (!IsSigned && TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(OpToUse, NewOutTy)) 0
2914 break; 0
2915 ----
2916 // Otherwise, try a larger type. ----
2917 } ----
2918 ----
2919 // Okay, we found the operation and type to use. ----
2920 SDValue Operation; 0
2921 if (IsStrict) { 0
2922 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(NewOutTy, MVT::Other); 0
2923 Operation = DAG.getNode(OpToUse, dl, VTs, N->getOperand(0), LegalOp); 0
2924 } else ----
2925 Operation = DAG.getNode(OpToUse, dl, NewOutTy, LegalOp); 0
2926 ----
2927 // Truncate the result of the extended FP_TO_*INT operation to the desired ----
2928 // size. ----
2929 SDValue Trunc = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, DestVT, Operation); 0
2930 Results.push_back(Trunc); 0
2931 if (IsStrict) 0
2932 Results.push_back(Operation.getValue(1)); 0
2933 } 0
2934 ----
2935 /// Promote FP_TO_*INT_SAT operation to a larger result type. At this point ----
2936 /// the result and operand types are legal and there must be a legal ----
2937 /// FP_TO_*INT_SAT operation for a larger result type. ----
2938 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::PromoteLegalFP_TO_INT_SAT(SDNode *Node, 0
2939 const SDLoc &dl) { ----
2940 unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode(); 0
2941 ----
2942 // Scan for the appropriate larger type to use. ----
2943 EVT NewOutTy = Node->getValueType(0); 0
2944 while (true) { ----
2945 NewOutTy = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(NewOutTy.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy + 1); 0
2946 assert(NewOutTy.isInteger() && "Ran out of possibilities!"); 0
2947 ----
2948 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(Opcode, NewOutTy)) 0
2949 break; 0
2950 } ----
2951 ----
2952 // Saturation width is determined by second operand, so we don't have to ----
2953 // perform any fixup and can directly truncate the result. ----
2954 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(Opcode, dl, NewOutTy, Node->getOperand(0), 0
2955 Node->getOperand(1)); 0
2956 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Result); 0
2957 } ----
2958 ----
2959 /// Open code the operations for PARITY of the specified operation. ----
2960 SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandPARITY(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &dl) { 0
2961 EVT VT = Op.getValueType(); 0
2962 EVT ShVT = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout()); 0
2963 unsigned Sz = VT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
2964 ----
2965 // If CTPOP is legal, use it. Otherwise use shifts and xor. ----
2966 SDValue Result; 0
2967 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrPromote(ISD::CTPOP, VT)) { 0
2968 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::CTPOP, dl, VT, Op); 0
2969 } else { ----
2970 Result = Op; 0
2971 for (unsigned i = Log2_32_Ceil(Sz); i != 0;) { 0
2972 SDValue Shift = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Result, 0
2973 DAG.getConstant(1ULL << (--i), dl, ShVT)); 0
2974 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, VT, Result, Shift); 0
2975 } ----
2976 } ----
2977 ----
2978 return DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Result, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT)); 0
2979 } ----
2980 ----
2981 bool SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandNode(SDNode *Node) { 0
2982 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying to expand node\n"); 0
2983 SmallVector Results; 0
2984 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
2985 SDValue Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4; 0
2986 bool NeedInvert; ----
2987 switch (Node->getOpcode()) { 0
2988 case ISD::ABS: 0
2989 if ((Tmp1 = TLI.expandABS(Node, DAG))) 0
2990 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
2991 break; 0
2992 case ISD::ABDS: 0
2993 case ISD::ABDU: ----
2994 if ((Tmp1 = TLI.expandABD(Node, DAG))) 0
2995 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
2996 break; 0
2997 case ISD::CTPOP: 0
2998 if ((Tmp1 = TLI.expandCTPOP(Node, DAG))) 0
2999 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3000 break; 0
3001 case ISD::CTLZ: 0
3002 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF: ----
3003 if ((Tmp1 = TLI.expandCTLZ(Node, DAG))) 0
3004 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3005 break; 0
3006 case ISD::CTTZ: 0
3007 case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF: ----
3008 if ((Tmp1 = TLI.expandCTTZ(Node, DAG))) 0
3009 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3010 break; 0
3011 case ISD::BITREVERSE: 0
3012 if ((Tmp1 = TLI.expandBITREVERSE(Node, DAG))) 0
3013 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3014 break; 0
3015 case ISD::BSWAP: 0
3016 if ((Tmp1 = TLI.expandBSWAP(Node, DAG))) 0
3017 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3018 break; 0
3019 case ISD::PARITY: 0
3020 Results.push_back(ExpandPARITY(Node->getOperand(0), dl)); 0
3021 break; 0
3022 case ISD::FRAMEADDR: 0
3023 case ISD::RETURNADDR: ----
3024 case ISD::FRAME_TO_ARGS_OFFSET: ----
3025 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(0))); 0
3026 break; 0
3027 case ISD::EH_DWARF_CFA: { 0
3028 SDValue CfaArg = DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Node->getOperand(0), dl, 0
3029 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())); 0
3030 SDValue Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, 0
3031 CfaArg.getValueType(), ----
3032 DAG.getNode(ISD::FRAME_TO_ARGS_OFFSET, dl, 0
3033 CfaArg.getValueType()), ----
3034 CfaArg); ----
3035 SDValue FA = DAG.getNode( 0
3036 ISD::FRAMEADDR, dl, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()), 0
3037 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout()))); 0
3038 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, FA.getValueType(), 0
3039 FA, Offset)); ----
3040 break; 0
3041 } ----
3042 case ISD::GET_ROUNDING: 0
3043 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstant(1, dl, Node->getValueType(0))); 0
3044 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(0)); 0
3045 break; 0
3046 case ISD::EH_RETURN: 0
3047 case ISD::EH_LABEL: ----
3048 case ISD::PREFETCH: ----
3049 case ISD::VAEND: ----
3050 case ISD::EH_SJLJ_LONGJMP: ----
3051 // If the target didn't expand these, there's nothing to do, so just ----
3052 // preserve the chain and be done. ----
3053 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(0)); 0
3054 break; 0
3055 case ISD::READCYCLECOUNTER: 0
3056 // If the target didn't expand this, just return 'zero' and preserve the ----
3057 // chain. ----
3058 Results.append(Node->getNumValues() - 1, 0
3059 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(0))); 0
3060 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(0)); 0
3061 break; 0
3062 case ISD::EH_SJLJ_SETJMP: 0
3063 // If the target didn't expand this, just return 'zero' and preserve the ----
3064 // chain. ----
3065 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstant(0, dl, MVT::i32)); 0
3066 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(0)); 0
3067 break; 0
3068 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD: { 0
3069 // There is no libcall for atomic load; fake it with ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP. ----
3070 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(0)); 0
3071 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other); 0
3072 SDValue Swap = DAG.getAtomicCmpSwap( 0
3073 ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, dl, cast(Node)->getMemoryVT(), VTs, 0
3074 Node->getOperand(0), Node->getOperand(1), Zero, Zero, 0
3075 cast(Node)->getMemOperand()); 0
3076 Results.push_back(Swap.getValue(0)); 0
3077 Results.push_back(Swap.getValue(1)); 0
3078 break; 0
3079 } ----
3080 case ISD::ATOMIC_STORE: { 0
3081 // There is no libcall for atomic store; fake it with ATOMIC_SWAP. ----
3082 SDValue Swap = DAG.getAtomic(ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP, dl, 0
3083 cast(Node)->getMemoryVT(), 0
3084 Node->getOperand(0), 0
3085 Node->getOperand(1), Node->getOperand(2), 0
3086 cast(Node)->getMemOperand()); 0
3087 Results.push_back(Swap.getValue(1)); 0
3088 break; 0
3089 } ----
3090 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS: { 0
3091 // Expanding an ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS produces an ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP and ----
3092 // splits out the success value as a comparison. Expanding the resulting ----
3093 // ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP will produce a libcall. ----
3094 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other); 0
3095 SDValue Res = DAG.getAtomicCmpSwap( 0
3096 ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, dl, cast(Node)->getMemoryVT(), VTs, 0
3097 Node->getOperand(0), Node->getOperand(1), Node->getOperand(2), 0
3098 Node->getOperand(3), cast(Node)->getMemOperand()); 0
3099 ----
3100 SDValue ExtRes = Res; 0
3101 SDValue LHS = Res; 0
3102 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1); 0
3103 ----
3104 EVT AtomicType = cast(Node)->getMemoryVT(); 0
3105 EVT OuterType = Node->getValueType(0); 0
3106 switch (TLI.getExtendForAtomicOps()) { 0
3107 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: 0
3108 LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, dl, OuterType, Res, 0
3109 DAG.getValueType(AtomicType)); 0
3110 RHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl, OuterType, 0
3111 Node->getOperand(2), DAG.getValueType(AtomicType)); 0
3112 ExtRes = LHS; 0
3113 break; 0
3114 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: 0
3115 LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, dl, OuterType, Res, 0
3116 DAG.getValueType(AtomicType)); 0
3117 RHS = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Node->getOperand(2), dl, AtomicType); 0
3118 ExtRes = LHS; 0
3119 break; 0
3120 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: 0
3121 LHS = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Res, dl, AtomicType); 0
3122 RHS = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Node->getOperand(2), dl, AtomicType); 0
3123 break; 0
3124 default: 0
3125 llvm_unreachable("Invalid atomic op extension"); 0
3126 } ----
3127 ----
3128 SDValue Success = ----
3129 DAG.getSetCC(dl, Node->getValueType(1), LHS, RHS, ISD::SETEQ); 0
3130 ----
3131 Results.push_back(ExtRes.getValue(0)); 0
3132 Results.push_back(Success); 0
3133 Results.push_back(Res.getValue(1)); 0
3134 break; 0
3135 } ----
3136 case ISD::DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC: 0
3137 ExpandDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC(Node, Results); 0
3138 break; 0
3139 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES: 0
3140 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Node->getNumValues(); i++) 0
3141 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(i)); 0
3142 break; 0
3143 case ISD::UNDEF: { 0
3144 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
3145 if (VT.isInteger()) 0
3146 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT)); 0
3147 else { ----
3148 assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() && "Unknown value type!"); 0
3149 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstantFP(0, dl, VT)); 0
3150 } ----
3151 break; 0
3152 } ----
3153 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND: 0
3154 // When strict mode is enforced we can't do expansion because it ----
3155 // does not honor the "strict" properties. Only libcall is allowed. ----
3156 if (TLI.isStrictFPEnabled()) 0
3157 break; 0
3158 // We might as well mutate to FP_ROUND when FP_ROUND operation is legal ----
3159 // since this operation is more efficient than stack operation. ----
3160 if (TLI.getStrictFPOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), 0
3161 Node->getValueType(0)) ----
3162 == TargetLowering::Legal) 0
3163 break; 0
3164 // We fall back to use stack operation when the FP_ROUND operation ----
3165 // isn't available. ----
3166 if ((Tmp1 = EmitStackConvert(Node->getOperand(1), Node->getValueType(0), 0
3167 Node->getValueType(0), dl, ----
3168 Node->getOperand(0)))) { 0
3169 ReplaceNode(Node, Tmp1.getNode()); 0
3170 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully expanded STRICT_FP_ROUND node\n"); 0
3171 return true; 0
3172 } ----
3173 break; 0
3174 case ISD::FP_ROUND: 0
3175 case ISD::BITCAST: ----
3176 if ((Tmp1 = EmitStackConvert(Node->getOperand(0), Node->getValueType(0), 0
3177 Node->getValueType(0), dl))) 0
3178 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3179 break; 0
3180 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND: 0
3181 // When strict mode is enforced we can't do expansion because it ----
3182 // does not honor the "strict" properties. Only libcall is allowed. ----
3183 if (TLI.isStrictFPEnabled()) 0
3184 break; 0
3185 // We might as well mutate to FP_EXTEND when FP_EXTEND operation is legal ----
3186 // since this operation is more efficient than stack operation. ----
3187 if (TLI.getStrictFPOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), 0
3188 Node->getValueType(0)) ----
3189 == TargetLowering::Legal) 0
3190 break; 0
3191 // We fall back to use stack operation when the FP_EXTEND operation ----
3192 // isn't available. ----
3193 if ((Tmp1 = EmitStackConvert( 0
3194 Node->getOperand(1), Node->getOperand(1).getValueType(), 0
3195 Node->getValueType(0), dl, Node->getOperand(0)))) { 0
3196 ReplaceNode(Node, Tmp1.getNode()); 0
3197 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully expanded STRICT_FP_EXTEND node\n"); 0
3198 return true; 0
3199 } ----
3200 break; 0
3201 case ISD::FP_EXTEND: 0
3202 if ((Tmp1 = EmitStackConvert(Node->getOperand(0), 0
3203 Node->getOperand(0).getValueType(), 0
3204 Node->getValueType(0), dl))) 0
3205 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3206 break; 0
3207 case ISD::BF16_TO_FP: { 0
3208 // Always expand bf16 to f32 casts, they lower to ext + shift. ----
3209 // ----
3210 // Note that the operand of this code can be bf16 or an integer type in case ----
3211 // bf16 is not supported on the target and was softened. ----
3212 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0); 0
3213 if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::bf16) { 0
3214 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, MVT::i32, 0
3215 DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, MVT::i16, Op)); 0
3216 } else { ----
3217 Op = DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Op, dl, MVT::i32); 0
3218 } ----
3219 Op = DAG.getNode( 0
3220 ISD::SHL, dl, MVT::i32, Op, ----
3221 DAG.getConstant(16, dl, 0
3222 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(MVT::i32, DAG.getDataLayout()))); 0
3223 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, MVT::f32, Op); 0
3224 // Add fp_extend in case the output is bigger than f32. ----
3225 if (Node->getValueType(0) != MVT::f32) 0
3226 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Op); 0
3227 Results.push_back(Op); 0
3228 break; 0
3229 } ----
3230 case ISD::FP_TO_BF16: { 0
3231 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(0); 0
3232 if (Op.getValueType() != MVT::f32) 0
3233 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, dl, MVT::f32, Op, 0
3234 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl, /*isTarget=*/true)); 0
3235 Op = DAG.getNode( 0
3236 ISD::SRL, dl, MVT::i32, DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, MVT::i32, Op), 0
3237 DAG.getConstant(16, dl, 0
3238 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(MVT::i32, DAG.getDataLayout()))); 0
3239 // The result of this node can be bf16 or an integer type in case bf16 is ----
3240 // not supported on the target and was softened to i16 for storage. ----
3241 if (Node->getValueType(0) == MVT::bf16) { 0
3242 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, MVT::bf16, 0
3243 DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, MVT::i16, Op)); 0
3244 } else { ----
3245 Op = DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Op, dl, Node->getValueType(0)); 0
3246 } ----
3247 Results.push_back(Op); 0
3248 break; 0
3249 } ----
3250 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: { 0
3251 EVT ExtraVT = cast(Node->getOperand(1))->getVT(); 0
3252 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
3253 ----
3254 // An in-register sign-extend of a boolean is a negation: ----
3255 // 'true' (1) sign-extended is -1. ----
3256 // 'false' (0) sign-extended is 0. ----
3257 // However, we must mask the high bits of the source operand because the ----
3258 // SIGN_EXTEND_INREG does not guarantee that the high bits are already zero. ----
3259 ----
3260 // TODO: Do this for vectors too? ----
3261 if (ExtraVT.isScalarInteger() && ExtraVT.getSizeInBits() == 1) { 0
3262 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT); 0
3263 SDValue And = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Node->getOperand(0), One); 0
3264 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT); 0
3265 SDValue Neg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Zero, And); 0
3266 Results.push_back(Neg); 0
3267 break; 0
3268 } ----
3269 ----
3270 // NOTE: we could fall back on load/store here too for targets without ----
3271 // SRA. However, it is doubtful that any exist. ----
3272 EVT ShiftAmountTy = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout()); 0
3273 unsigned BitsDiff = VT.getScalarSizeInBits() - 0
3274 ExtraVT.getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
3275 SDValue ShiftCst = DAG.getConstant(BitsDiff, dl, ShiftAmountTy); 0
3276 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, Node->getValueType(0), 0
3277 Node->getOperand(0), ShiftCst); 0
3278 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, ShiftCst); 0
3279 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3280 break; 0
3281 } ----
3282 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: 0
3283 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP: ----
3284 if (TLI.expandUINT_TO_FP(Node, Tmp1, Tmp2, DAG)) { 0
3285 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3286 if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) 0
3287 Results.push_back(Tmp2); 0
3288 break; 0
3289 } ----
3290 [[fallthrough]]; ----
3291 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: ----
3292 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP: ----
3293 if ((Tmp1 = ExpandLegalINT_TO_FP(Node, Tmp2))) { 0
3294 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3295 if (Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) 0
3296 Results.push_back(Tmp2); 0
3297 } ----
3298 break; 0
3299 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT: 0
3300 if (TLI.expandFP_TO_SINT(Node, Tmp1, DAG)) 0
3301 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3302 break; 0
3303 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT: 0
3304 if (TLI.expandFP_TO_SINT(Node, Tmp1, DAG)) { 0
3305 ReplaceNode(Node, Tmp1.getNode()); 0
3306 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully expanded STRICT_FP_TO_SINT node\n"); 0
3307 return true; 0
3308 } ----
3309 break; 0
3310 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: 0
3311 if (TLI.expandFP_TO_UINT(Node, Tmp1, Tmp2, DAG)) 0
3312 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3313 break; 0
3314 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT: 0
3315 if (TLI.expandFP_TO_UINT(Node, Tmp1, Tmp2, DAG)) { 0
3316 // Relink the chain. ----
3317 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node,1), Tmp2); 0
3318 // Replace the new UINT result. ----
3319 ReplaceNodeWithValue(SDValue(Node, 0), Tmp1); 0
3320 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully expanded STRICT_FP_TO_UINT node\n"); 0
3321 return true; 0
3322 } ----
3323 break; 0
3324 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT: 0
3325 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT: ----
3326 Results.push_back(TLI.expandFP_TO_INT_SAT(Node, DAG)); 0
3327 break; 0
3328 case ISD::VAARG: 0
3329 Results.push_back(DAG.expandVAArg(Node)); 0
3330 Results.push_back(Results[0].getValue(1)); 0
3331 break; 0
3332 case ISD::VACOPY: 0
3333 Results.push_back(DAG.expandVACopy(Node)); 0
3334 break; 0
3335 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: 0
3336 if (Node->getOperand(0).getValueType().getVectorNumElements() == 1) 0
3337 // This must be an access of the only element. Return it. ----
3338 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, Node->getValueType(0), 0
3339 Node->getOperand(0)); 0
3340 else ----
3341 Tmp1 = ExpandExtractFromVectorThroughStack(SDValue(Node, 0)); 0
3342 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3343 break; 0
3344 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: 0
3345 Results.push_back(ExpandExtractFromVectorThroughStack(SDValue(Node, 0))); 0
3346 break; 0
3347 case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: 0
3348 Results.push_back(ExpandInsertToVectorThroughStack(SDValue(Node, 0))); 0
3349 break; 0
3350 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: 0
3351 Results.push_back(ExpandVectorBuildThroughStack(Node)); 0
3352 break; 0
3353 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: 0
3354 Results.push_back(ExpandSCALAR_TO_VECTOR(Node)); 0
3355 break; 0
3356 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: 0
3357 Results.push_back(ExpandINSERT_VECTOR_ELT(Node->getOperand(0), 0
3358 Node->getOperand(1), 0
3359 Node->getOperand(2), dl)); 0
3360 break; 0
3361 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: { 0
3362 SmallVector NewMask; 0
3363 ArrayRef Mask = cast(Node)->getMask(); 0
3364 ----
3365 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
3366 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType(); 0
3367 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
3368 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
3369 if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(EltVT)) { 0
3370 EVT NewEltVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT); 0
3371 ----
3372 // BUILD_VECTOR operands are allowed to be wider than the element type. ----
3373 // But if NewEltVT is smaller that EltVT the BUILD_VECTOR does not accept ----
3374 // it. ----
3375 if (NewEltVT.bitsLT(EltVT)) { 0
3376 // Convert shuffle node. ----
3377 // If original node was v4i64 and the new EltVT is i32, ----
3378 // cast operands to v8i32 and re-build the mask. ----
3379 ----
3380 // Calculate new VT, the size of the new VT should be equal to original. ----
3381 EVT NewVT = ----
3382 EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewEltVT, 0
3383 VT.getSizeInBits() / NewEltVT.getSizeInBits()); 0
3384 assert(NewVT.bitsEq(VT)); 0
3385 ----
3386 // cast operands to new VT ----
3387 Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, Op0); 0
3388 Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, Op1); 0
3389 ----
3390 // Convert the shuffle mask ----
3391 unsigned int factor = ----
3392 NewVT.getVectorNumElements()/VT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
3393 ----
3394 // EltVT gets smaller ----
3395 assert(factor > 0); 0
3396 ----
3397 for (unsigned i = 0; i < VT.getVectorNumElements(); ++i) { 0
3398 if (Mask[i] < 0) { 0
3399 for (unsigned fi = 0; fi < factor; ++fi) 0
3400 NewMask.push_back(Mask[i]); 0
3401 } ----
3402 else { ----
3403 for (unsigned fi = 0; fi < factor; ++fi) 0
3404 NewMask.push_back(Mask[i]*factor+fi); 0
3405 } ----
3406 } ----
3407 Mask = NewMask; 0
3408 VT = NewVT; 0
3409 } ----
3410 EltVT = NewEltVT; 0
3411 } ----
3412 unsigned NumElems = VT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
3413 SmallVector Ops; 0
3414 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElems; ++i) { 0
3415 if (Mask[i] < 0) { 0
3416 Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT)); 0
3417 continue; 0
3418 } ----
3419 unsigned Idx = Mask[i]; 0
3420 if (Idx < NumElems) 0
3421 Ops.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, Op0, 0
3422 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl))); 0
3423 else ----
3424 Ops.push_back( 0
3425 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, Op1, 0
3426 DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx - NumElems, dl))); 0
3427 } ----
3428 ----
3429 Tmp1 = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Ops); 0

3808 case ISD::UADDO_CARRY: 0
3809 case ISD::USUBO_CARRY: { ----
3810 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0); 0
3811 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1); 0
3812 SDValue Carry = Node->getOperand(2); 0
3813 ----
3814 bool IsAdd = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UADDO_CARRY; 0
3815 ----
3816 // Initial add of the 2 operands. ----
3817 unsigned Op = IsAdd ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB; 0
3818 EVT VT = LHS.getValueType(); 0
3819 SDValue Sum = DAG.getNode(Op, dl, VT, LHS, RHS); 0
3820 ----
3821 // Initial check for overflow. ----
3822 EVT CarryType = Node->getValueType(1); 0
3823 EVT SetCCType = getSetCCResultType(Node->getValueType(0)); 0
3824 ISD::CondCode CC = IsAdd ? ISD::SETULT : ISD::SETUGT; 0
3825 SDValue Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Sum, LHS, CC); 0
3826 ----
3827 // Add of the sum and the carry. ----
3828 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT); 0
3829 SDValue CarryExt = ----
3830 DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Carry, dl, VT), One); 0
3831 SDValue Sum2 = DAG.getNode(Op, dl, VT, Sum, CarryExt); 0
3832 ----
3833 // Second check for overflow. If we are adding, we can only overflow if the ----
3834 // initial sum is all 1s ang the carry is set, resulting in a new sum of 0. ----
3835 // If we are subtracting, we can only overflow if the initial sum is 0 and ----
3836 // the carry is set, resulting in a new sum of all 1s. ----
3837 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT); 0
3838 SDValue Overflow2 = ----
3839 IsAdd ? DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Sum2, Zero, ISD::SETEQ) 0
3840 : DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Sum, Zero, ISD::SETEQ); 0
3841 Overflow2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, SetCCType, Overflow2, 0
3842 DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Carry, dl, SetCCType)); 0
3843 ----

3845 DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, SetCCType, Overflow, Overflow2); 0
3846 ----
3847 Results.push_back(Sum2); 0
3848 Results.push_back(DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(ResultCarry, dl, CarryType, VT)); 0
3849 break; 0

3903 case ISD::BR_JT: { 0
3904 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); 0
3905 SDValue Table = Node->getOperand(1); 0
3906 SDValue Index = Node->getOperand(2); 0
3907 ----
3908 const DataLayout &TD = DAG.getDataLayout(); 0
3909 EVT PTy = TLI.getPointerTy(TD); 0
3910 ----
3911 unsigned EntrySize = ----
3912 DAG.getMachineFunction().getJumpTableInfo()->getEntrySize(TD); 0
3913 ----
3914 // For power-of-two jumptable entry sizes convert multiplication to a shift. ----
3915 // This transformation needs to be done here since otherwise the MIPS ----
3916 // backend will end up emitting a three instruction multiply sequence ----
3917 // instead of a single shift and MSP430 will call a runtime function. ----
3918 if (llvm::isPowerOf2_32(EntrySize)) 0
3919 Index = DAG.getNode( 0
3920 ISD::SHL, dl, Index.getValueType(), Index, ----
3921 DAG.getConstant(llvm::Log2_32(EntrySize), dl, Index.getValueType())); 0
3922 else ----
3923 Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, Index.getValueType(), Index, 0
3924 DAG.getConstant(EntrySize, dl, Index.getValueType())); 0
3925 SDValue Addr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, Index.getValueType(), 0
3926 Index, Table); ----
3927 ----
3928 EVT MemVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), EntrySize * 8); 0
3929 SDValue LD = DAG.getExtLoad( 0
3930 ISD::SEXTLOAD, dl, PTy, Chain, Addr, ----
3931 MachinePointerInfo::getJumpTable(DAG.getMachineFunction()), MemVT); 0
3932 Addr = LD; 0
3933 if (TLI.isJumpTableRelative()) { 0
3934 // For PIC, the sequence is: ----
3935 // BRIND(load(Jumptable + index) + RelocBase) ----
3936 // RelocBase can be JumpTable, GOT or some sort of global base. ----
3937 Addr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, PTy, Addr, 0
3938 TLI.getPICJumpTableRelocBase(Table, DAG)); 0
3939 } ----
3940 ----
3941 Tmp1 = TLI.expandIndirectJTBranch(dl, LD.getValue(1), Addr, DAG); 0
3942 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3943 break; 0
3944 } ----
3945 case ISD::BRCOND: 0
3946 // Expand brcond's setcc into its constituent parts and create a BR_CC ----
3947 // Node. ----
3948 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
3949 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
3950 if (Tmp2.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC && 0
3951 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::BR_CC, 0
3952 Tmp2.getOperand(0).getValueType())) { 0
3953 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, MVT::Other, Tmp1, Tmp2.getOperand(2), 0
3954 Tmp2.getOperand(0), Tmp2.getOperand(1), 0
3955 Node->getOperand(2)); 0
3956 } else { ----
3957 // We test only the i1 bit. Skip the AND if UNDEF or another AND. ----
3958 if (Tmp2.isUndef() || 0
3959 (Tmp2.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && isOneConstant(Tmp2.getOperand(1)))) 0
3960 Tmp3 = Tmp2; 0
3961 else ----
3962 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, Tmp2.getValueType(), Tmp2, 0
3963 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, Tmp2.getValueType())); 0
3964 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, MVT::Other, Tmp1, 0
3965 DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE), Tmp3, 0
3966 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Tmp3.getValueType()), 0
3967 Node->getOperand(2)); 0
3968 } ----
3969 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
3970 break; 0
3971 case ISD::SETCC: 0
3972 case ISD::VP_SETCC: ----
3973 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC: ----
3974 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS: { ----
3975 bool IsVP = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::VP_SETCC; 0
3976 bool IsStrict = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FSETCC || 0
3977 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS; 0
3978 bool IsSignaling = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS; 0
3979 SDValue Chain = IsStrict ? Node->getOperand(0) : SDValue(); 0
3980 unsigned Offset = IsStrict ? 1 : 0; 0
3981 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0 + Offset); 0
3982 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1 + Offset); 0
3983 Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(2 + Offset); 0
3984 SDValue Mask, EVL; 0
3985 if (IsVP) { 0
3986 Mask = Node->getOperand(3 + Offset); 0
3987 EVL = Node->getOperand(4 + Offset); 0
3988 } ----
3989 bool Legalized = TLI.LegalizeSetCCCondCode( 0
3990 DAG, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Mask, EVL, NeedInvert, dl, ----
3991 Chain, IsSignaling); ----
3992 ----
3993 if (Legalized) { 0
3994 // If we expanded the SETCC by swapping LHS and RHS, or by inverting the ----
3995 // condition code, create a new SETCC node. ----
3996 if (Tmp3.getNode()) { 0
3997 if (IsStrict) { 0
3998 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, Node->getVTList(), 0
3999 {Chain, Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3}, Node->getFlags()); ----
4000 Chain = Tmp1.getValue(1); 0
4001 } else if (IsVP) { 0
4002 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, Node->getValueType(0), 0
4003 {Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Mask, EVL}, Node->getFlags()); ----
4004 } else { ----
4005 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, 0
4006 Tmp2, Tmp3, Node->getFlags()); ----
4007 } ----
4008 } ----
4009 ----
4010 // If we expanded the SETCC by inverting the condition code, then wrap ----
4011 // the existing SETCC in a NOT to restore the intended condition. ----
4012 if (NeedInvert) { 0
4013 if (!IsVP) 0
4014 Tmp1 = DAG.getLogicalNOT(dl, Tmp1, Tmp1->getValueType(0)); 0
4015 else ----
4016 Tmp1 = 0
4017 DAG.getVPLogicalNOT(dl, Tmp1, Mask, EVL, Tmp1->getValueType(0)); 0
4018 } ----
4019 ----
4020 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
4021 if (IsStrict) 0
4022 Results.push_back(Chain); 0
4023 ----
4024 break; 0
4025 } ----
4026 ----
4027 // FIXME: It seems Legalized is false iff CCCode is Legal. I don't ----
4028 // understand if this code is useful for strict nodes. ----
4029 assert(!IsStrict && "Don't know how to expand for strict nodes."); 0
4030 ----
4031 // Otherwise, SETCC for the given comparison type must be completely ----
4032 // illegal; expand it into a SELECT_CC. ----
4033 // FIXME: This drops the mask/evl for VP_SETCC. ----
4034 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
4035 EVT Tmp1VT = Tmp1.getValueType(); 0
4036 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, dl, VT, Tmp1, Tmp2, 0
4037 DAG.getBoolConstant(true, dl, VT, Tmp1VT), 0
4038 DAG.getBoolConstant(false, dl, VT, Tmp1VT), Tmp3); 0
4039 Tmp1->setFlags(Node->getFlags()); 0
4040 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
4041 break; 0
4042 } ----
4043 case ISD::SELECT_CC: { 0
4044 // TODO: need to add STRICT_SELECT_CC and STRICT_SELECT_CCS ----
4045 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0); // LHS 0
4046 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1); // RHS 0
4047 Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(2); // True 0
4048 Tmp4 = Node->getOperand(3); // False 0
4049 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
4050 SDValue Chain; 0
4051 SDValue CC = Node->getOperand(4); 0
4052 ISD::CondCode CCOp = cast(CC)->get(); 0
4053 ----
4054 if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(CCOp, Tmp1.getSimpleValueType())) { 0
4055 // If the condition code is legal, then we need to expand this ----
4056 // node using SETCC and SELECT. ----
4057 EVT CmpVT = Tmp1.getValueType(); 0
4058 assert(!TLI.isOperationExpand(ISD::SELECT, VT) && 0
4059 "Cannot expand ISD::SELECT_CC when ISD::SELECT also needs to be " ----
4060 "expanded."); ----
4061 EVT CCVT = getSetCCResultType(CmpVT); 0
4062 SDValue Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, dl, CCVT, Tmp1, Tmp2, CC, Node->getFlags()); 0
4063 Results.push_back(DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Cond, Tmp3, Tmp4)); 0
4064 break; 0
4065 } ----
4066 ----
4067 // SELECT_CC is legal, so the condition code must not be. ----
4068 bool Legalized = false; 0
4069 // Try to legalize by inverting the condition. This is for targets that ----
4070 // might support an ordered version of a condition, but not the unordered ----
4071 // version (or vice versa). ----
4072 ISD::CondCode InvCC = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCOp, Tmp1.getValueType()); 0
4073 if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(InvCC, Tmp1.getSimpleValueType())) { 0
4074 // Use the new condition code and swap true and false ----
4075 Legalized = true; 0
4076 Tmp1 = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp4, Tmp3, InvCC); 0
4077 Tmp1->setFlags(Node->getFlags()); 0
4078 } else { ----
4079 // If The inverse is not legal, then try to swap the arguments using ----
4080 // the inverse condition code. ----
4081 ISD::CondCode SwapInvCC = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(InvCC); 0
4082 if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(SwapInvCC, Tmp1.getSimpleValueType())) { 0
4083 // The swapped inverse condition is legal, so swap true and false, ----
4084 // lhs and rhs. ----
4085 Legalized = true; 0
4086 Tmp1 = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Tmp2, Tmp1, Tmp4, Tmp3, SwapInvCC); 0
4087 Tmp1->setFlags(Node->getFlags()); 0
4088 } ----
4089 } ----
4090 ----
4091 if (!Legalized) { 0
4092 Legalized = TLI.LegalizeSetCCCondCode( 0
4093 DAG, getSetCCResultType(Tmp1.getValueType()), Tmp1, Tmp2, CC, ----
4094 /*Mask*/ SDValue(), /*EVL*/ SDValue(), NeedInvert, dl, Chain); ----
4095 ----
4096 assert(Legalized && "Can't legalize SELECT_CC with legal condition!"); 0
4097 ----
4098 // If we expanded the SETCC by inverting the condition code, then swap ----
4099 // the True/False operands to match. ----
4100 if (NeedInvert) 0
4101 std::swap(Tmp3, Tmp4); 0
4102 ----
4103 // If we expanded the SETCC by swapping LHS and RHS, or by inverting the ----
4104 // condition code, create a new SELECT_CC node. ----
4105 if (CC.getNode()) { 0
4106 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), 0
4107 Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, CC); ----
4108 } else { ----
4109 Tmp2 = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Tmp1.getValueType()); 0
4110 CC = DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE); 0
4111 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, 0
4112 Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, CC); ----
4113 } ----
4114 Tmp1->setFlags(Node->getFlags()); 0
4115 } ----
4116 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
4117 break; 0
4118 } ----
4119 case ISD::BR_CC: { 0
4120 // TODO: need to add STRICT_BR_CC and STRICT_BR_CCS ----
4121 SDValue Chain; 0
4122 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0); // Chain 0
4123 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(2); // LHS 0
4124 Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(3); // RHS 0
4125 Tmp4 = Node->getOperand(1); // CC 0
4126 ----
4127 bool Legalized = TLI.LegalizeSetCCCondCode( 0
4128 DAG, getSetCCResultType(Tmp2.getValueType()), Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, ----
4129 /*Mask*/ SDValue(), /*EVL*/ SDValue(), NeedInvert, dl, Chain); ----
4130 (void)Legalized; ----
4131 assert(Legalized && "Can't legalize BR_CC with legal condition!"); 0
4132 ----
4133 // If we expanded the SETCC by swapping LHS and RHS, create a new BR_CC ----
4134 // node. ----
4135 if (Tmp4.getNode()) { 0
4136 assert(!NeedInvert && "Don't know how to invert BR_CC!"); 0
4137 ----
4138 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, 0
4139 Tmp4, Tmp2, Tmp3, Node->getOperand(4)); 0
4140 } else { ----
4141 Tmp3 = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Tmp2.getValueType()); 0
4142 Tmp4 = DAG.getCondCode(NeedInvert ? ISD::SETEQ : ISD::SETNE); 0
4143 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, Tmp4, 0
4144 Tmp2, Tmp3, Node->getOperand(4)); 0
4145 } ----
4146 Results.push_back(Tmp1); 0
4147 break; 0
4148 } ----
4149 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: 0
4150 Results.push_back(ExpandBUILD_VECTOR(Node)); 0
4151 break; 0
4152 case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR: 0
4153 Results.push_back(ExpandSPLAT_VECTOR(Node)); 0
4154 break; 0
4155 case ISD::SRA: 0
4156 case ISD::SRL: ----
4157 case ISD::SHL: { ----
4158 // Scalarize vector SRA/SRL/SHL. ----
4159 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
4160 assert(VT.isVector() && "Unable to legalize non-vector shift"); 0
4161 assert(TLI.isTypeLegal(VT.getScalarType())&& "Element type must be legal"); 0
4162 unsigned NumElem = VT.getVectorNumElements(); 0
4163 ----
4164 SmallVector Scalars; 0
4165 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; Idx++) { 0
4166 SDValue Ex = ----
4167 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, VT.getScalarType(), 0
4168 Node->getOperand(0), DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl)); 0
4169 SDValue Sh = ----
4170 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, VT.getScalarType(), 0
4171 Node->getOperand(1), DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(Idx, dl)); 0
4172 Scalars.push_back(DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, 0
4173 VT.getScalarType(), Ex, Sh)); ----
4174 } ----
4175 ----
4176 SDValue Result = DAG.getBuildVector(Node->getValueType(0), dl, Scalars); 0
4177 Results.push_back(Result); 0
4178 break; 0
4179 } 0
4180 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD: 0
4181 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL: ----
4182 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD: ----
4183 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL: ----
4184 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND: ----
4185 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR: ----
4186 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR: ----
4187 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX: ----
4188 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN: ----
4189 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX: ----
4190 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN: ----
4191 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX: ----
4192 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN: ----
4193 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAXIMUM: ----
4194 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMINIMUM: ----
4195 Results.push_back(TLI.expandVecReduce(Node, DAG)); 0
4196 break; 0
4197 case ISD::GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE: 0
4198 case ISD::GlobalAddress: ----
4199 case ISD::GlobalTLSAddress: ----
4200 case ISD::ExternalSymbol: ----
4201 case ISD::ConstantPool: ----
4202 case ISD::JumpTable: ----
4203 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: ----
4204 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: ----
4205 case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID: ----
4206 // FIXME: Custom lowering for these operations shouldn't return null! ----
4207 // Return true so that we don't call ConvertNodeToLibcall which also won't ----
4208 // do anything. ----
4209 return true; 0
4210 } ----
4211 ----
4212 if (!TLI.isStrictFPEnabled() && Results.empty() && Node->isStrictFPOpcode()) { 0
4213 // FIXME: We were asked to expand a strict floating-point operation, ----
4214 // but there is currently no expansion implemented that would preserve ----
4215 // the "strict" properties. For now, we just fall back to the non-strict ----
4216 // version if that is legal on the target. The actual mutation of the ----
4217 // operation will happen in SelectionDAGISel::DoInstructionSelection. ----
4218 switch (Node->getOpcode()) { 0
4219 default: 0
4220 if (TLI.getStrictFPOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), 0
4221 Node->getValueType(0)) ----
4222 == TargetLowering::Legal) 0
4223 return true; 0
4224 break; 0
4225 case ISD::STRICT_FSUB: { 0
4226 if (TLI.getStrictFPOperationAction( 0
4227 ISD::STRICT_FSUB, Node->getValueType(0)) == TargetLowering::Legal) 0
4228 return true; 0
4229 if (TLI.getStrictFPOperationAction( 0
4230 ISD::STRICT_FADD, Node->getValueType(0)) != TargetLowering::Legal) 0
4231 break; 0
4232 ----
4233 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
4234 const SDNodeFlags Flags = Node->getFlags(); 0
4235 SDValue Neg = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, dl, VT, Node->getOperand(2), Flags); 0
4236 SDValue Fadd = DAG.getNode(ISD::STRICT_FADD, dl, Node->getVTList(), 0
4237 {Node->getOperand(0), Node->getOperand(1), Neg}, 0
4238 Flags); ----
4239 ----
4240 Results.push_back(Fadd); 0
4241 Results.push_back(Fadd.getValue(1)); 0
4242 break; 0
4243 } ----
4244 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP: 0
4245 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP: ----
4246 case ISD::STRICT_LRINT: ----
4247 case ISD::STRICT_LLRINT: ----
4248 case ISD::STRICT_LROUND: ----
4249 case ISD::STRICT_LLROUND: ----
4250 // These are registered by the operand type instead of the value ----
4251 // type. Reflect that here. ----
4252 if (TLI.getStrictFPOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), 0
4253 Node->getOperand(1).getValueType()) 0
4254 == TargetLowering::Legal) 0
4255 return true; 0
4256 break; 0
4257 } ----
4258 } ----
4259 ----
4260 // Replace the original node with the legalized result. ----
4261 if (Results.empty()) { 0
4262 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cannot expand node\n"); 0
4263 return false; 0
4264 } ----
4265 ----
4266 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully expanded node\n"); 0
4267 ReplaceNode(Node, Results.data()); 0
4268 return true; 0
4269 } 0
4270 ----
4271 void SelectionDAGLegalize::ConvertNodeToLibcall(SDNode *Node) { 0
4272 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying to convert node to libcall\n"); 0
4273 SmallVector Results; 0
4274 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
4275 // FIXME: Check flags on the node to see if we can use a finite call. ----
4276 unsigned Opc = Node->getOpcode(); 0
4277 switch (Opc) { 0
4278 case ISD::ATOMIC_FENCE: { 0
4279 // If the target didn't lower this, lower it to '__sync_synchronize()' call ----
4280 // FIXME: handle "fence singlethread" more efficiently. ----
4281 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args; 0
4282 ----
4283 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG); 0
4284 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl) 0
4285 .setChain(Node->getOperand(0)) 0
4286 .setLibCallee( 0
4287 CallingConv::C, Type::getVoidTy(*DAG.getContext()), 0
4288 DAG.getExternalSymbol("__sync_synchronize", 0
4289 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())), 0
4290 std::move(Args)); 0
4291 ----
4292 std::pair CallResult = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI); 0
4293 ----
4294 Results.push_back(CallResult.second); 0
4295 break; 0
4296 } 0
4297 // By default, atomic intrinsics are marked Legal and lowered. Targets ----
4298 // which don't support them directly, however, may want libcalls, in which ----
4299 // case they mark them Expand, and we get here. ----
4300 case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP: 0
4301 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD: ----
4302 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB: ----
4303 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND: ----
4304 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_CLR: ----
4305 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR: ----
4306 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR: ----
4307 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND: ----
4308 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN: ----
4309 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX: ----
4310 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN: ----
4311 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX: ----
4312 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP: { ----
4313 MVT VT = cast(Node)->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT(); 0
4314 AtomicOrdering Order = cast(Node)->getMergedOrdering(); 0
4315 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::getOUTLINE_ATOMIC(Opc, Order, VT); 0
4316 EVT RetVT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
4317 TargetLowering::MakeLibCallOptions CallOptions; 0
4318 SmallVector Ops; 0
4319 if (TLI.getLibcallName(LC)) { 0
4320 // If outline atomic available, prepare its arguments and expand. ----
4321 Ops.append(Node->op_begin() + 2, Node->op_end()); 0
4322 Ops.push_back(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
4323 ----
4324 } else { ----
4325 LC = RTLIB::getSYNC(Opc, VT); 0
4326 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && 0
4327 "Unexpected atomic op or value type!"); ----
4328 // Arguments for expansion to sync libcall ----
4329 Ops.append(Node->op_begin() + 1, Node->op_end()); 0
4330 } ----
4331 std::pair Tmp = TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, RetVT, 0
4332 Ops, CallOptions, ----
4333 SDLoc(Node), 0
4334 Node->getOperand(0)); 0
4335 Results.push_back(Tmp.first); 0
4336 Results.push_back(Tmp.second); 0
4337 break; 0
4338 } 0
4339 case ISD::TRAP: { 0
4340 // If this operation is not supported, lower it to 'abort()' call ----
4341 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args; 0
4342 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG); 0
4343 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl) 0
4344 .setChain(Node->getOperand(0)) 0
4345 .setLibCallee(CallingConv::C, Type::getVoidTy(*DAG.getContext()), 0
4346 DAG.getExternalSymbol( 0
4347 "abort", TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout())), 0
4348 std::move(Args)); 0
4349 std::pair CallResult = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI); 0
4350 ----
4351 Results.push_back(CallResult.second); 0
4352 break; 0
4353 } 0
4354 case ISD::FMINNUM: 0
4355 case ISD::STRICT_FMINNUM: ----
4356 ExpandFPLibCall(Node, RTLIB::FMIN_F32, RTLIB::FMIN_F64, 0
4357 RTLIB::FMIN_F80, RTLIB::FMIN_F128, ----
4358 RTLIB::FMIN_PPCF128, Results); ----
4359 break; 0
4360 // FIXME: We do not have libcalls for FMAXIMUM and FMINIMUM. So, we cannot use ----
4361 // libcall legalization for these nodes, but there is no default expasion for ----
4362 // these nodes either (see PR63267 for example). ----
4363 case ISD::FMAXNUM: 0
4364 case ISD::STRICT_FMAXNUM: ----
4365 ExpandFPLibCall(Node, RTLIB::FMAX_F32, RTLIB::FMAX_F64, 0
4366 RTLIB::FMAX_F80, RTLIB::FMAX_F128, ----
4367 RTLIB::FMAX_PPCF128, Results); ----
4368 break; 0
4369 case ISD::FSQRT: 0
4370 case ISD::STRICT_FSQRT: ----
4371 ExpandFPLibCall(Node, RTLIB::SQRT_F32, RTLIB::SQRT_F64, 0
4372 RTLIB::SQRT_F80, RTLIB::SQRT_F128, ----
4373 RTLIB::SQRT_PPCF128, Results); ----
4374 break; 0
4375 case ISD::FCBRT: 0
4376 ExpandFPLibCall(Node, RTLIB::CBRT_F32, RTLIB::CBRT_F64, 0
4377 RTLIB::CBRT_F80, RTLIB::CBRT_F128, ----
4378 RTLIB::CBRT_PPCF128, Results); ----
4379 break; 0
4380 case ISD::FSIN: 0
4381 case ISD::STRICT_FSIN: ----
4382 ExpandFPLibCall(Node, RTLIB::SIN_F32, RTLIB::SIN_F64, 0
4383 RTLIB::SIN_F80, RTLIB::SIN_F128, ----
4384 RTLIB::SIN_PPCF128, Results); ----
4385 break; 0
4386 case ISD::FCOS: 0
4387 case ISD::STRICT_FCOS: ----
4388 ExpandFPLibCall(Node, RTLIB::COS_F32, RTLIB::COS_F64, 0
4389 RTLIB::COS_F80, RTLIB::COS_F128, ----
4390 RTLIB::COS_PPCF128, Results); ----
4391 break; 0
4392 case ISD::FSINCOS: 0
4393 // Expand into sincos libcall. ----
4394 ExpandSinCosLibCall(Node, Results); 0
4395 break; 0
4396 case ISD::FLOG: 0
4397 case ISD::STRICT_FLOG: ----
4398 ExpandFPLibCall(Node, RTLIB::LOG_F32, RTLIB::LOG_F64, RTLIB::LOG_F80, 0
4399 RTLIB::LOG_F128, RTLIB::LOG_PPCF128, Results); ----
4400 break; 0
4401 case ISD::FLOG2: 0

4610 break; 0

4612 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP: 0
4613 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP: ----
4614 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: ----
4615 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: { ----
4616 // TODO - Common the code with DAGTypeLegalizer::SoftenFloatRes_XINT_TO_FP ----
4617 bool IsStrict = Node->isStrictFPOpcode(); 0
4618 bool Signed = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SINT_TO_FP || 0
4619 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP; 0
4620 EVT SVT = Node->getOperand(IsStrict ? 1 : 0).getValueType(); 0
4621 EVT RVT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
4622 EVT NVT = EVT(); 0
4623 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
4624 ----
4625 // Even if the input is legal, no libcall may exactly match, eg. we don't ----
4626 // have i1 -> fp conversions. So, it needs to be promoted to a larger type, ----
4627 // eg: i13 -> fp. Then, look for an appropriate libcall. ----
4628 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL; 0
4629 for (unsigned t = MVT::FIRST_INTEGER_VALUETYPE; 0
4630 t <= MVT::LAST_INTEGER_VALUETYPE && LC == RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL; 0
4631 ++t) { ----
4632 NVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)t; 0
4633 // The source needs to big enough to hold the operand. ----
4634 if (NVT.bitsGE(SVT)) 0
4635 LC = Signed ? RTLIB::getSINTTOFP(NVT, RVT) 0
4636 : RTLIB::getUINTTOFP(NVT, RVT); 0
4637 } ----
4638 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Unable to legalize as libcall"); 0
4639 ----
4640 SDValue Chain = IsStrict ? Node->getOperand(0) : SDValue(); 0
4641 // Sign/zero extend the argument if the libcall takes a larger type. ----
4642 SDValue Op = DAG.getNode(Signed ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, 0
4643 NVT, Node->getOperand(IsStrict ? 1 : 0)); 0
4644 TargetLowering::MakeLibCallOptions CallOptions; 0
4645 CallOptions.setSExt(Signed); 0
4646 std::pair Tmp = ----
4647 TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, RVT, Op, CallOptions, dl, Chain); 0
4648 Results.push_back(Tmp.first); 0
4649 if (IsStrict) 0
4650 Results.push_back(Tmp.second); 0
4651 break; 0
4652 } 0
4653 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT: 0
4654 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: ----
4655 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT: ----
4656 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT: { ----
4657 // TODO - Common the code with DAGTypeLegalizer::SoftenFloatOp_FP_TO_XINT. ----
4658 bool IsStrict = Node->isStrictFPOpcode(); 0
4659 bool Signed = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT || 0
4660 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT; 0
4661 ----
4662 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(IsStrict ? 1 : 0); 0
4663 EVT SVT = Op.getValueType(); 0
4664 EVT RVT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
4665 EVT NVT = EVT(); 0
4666 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
4667 ----
4668 // Even if the result is legal, no libcall may exactly match, eg. we don't ----
4669 // have fp -> i1 conversions. So, it needs to be promoted to a larger type, ----
4670 // eg: fp -> i32. Then, look for an appropriate libcall. ----
4671 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL; 0
4672 for (unsigned IntVT = MVT::FIRST_INTEGER_VALUETYPE; 0
4673 IntVT <= MVT::LAST_INTEGER_VALUETYPE && LC == RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL; 0
4674 ++IntVT) { ----
4675 NVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)IntVT; 0
4676 // The type needs to big enough to hold the result. ----
4677 if (NVT.bitsGE(RVT)) 0
4678 LC = Signed ? RTLIB::getFPTOSINT(SVT, NVT) 0
4679 : RTLIB::getFPTOUINT(SVT, NVT); 0
4680 } ----
4681 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Unable to legalize as libcall"); 0
4682 ----
4683 SDValue Chain = IsStrict ? Node->getOperand(0) : SDValue(); 0
4684 TargetLowering::MakeLibCallOptions CallOptions; 0
4685 std::pair Tmp = ----
4686 TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, NVT, Op, CallOptions, dl, Chain); 0
4687 ----
4688 // Truncate the result if the libcall returns a larger type. ----
4689 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, RVT, Tmp.first)); 0
4690 if (IsStrict) 0
4691 Results.push_back(Tmp.second); 0
4692 break; 0
4693 } 0
4694 ----
4695 case ISD::FP_ROUND: 0
4696 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND: { ----
4697 // X = FP_ROUND(Y, TRUNC) ----
4698 // TRUNC is a flag, which is always an integer that is zero or one. ----
4699 // If TRUNC is 0, this is a normal rounding, if it is 1, this FP_ROUND ----
4700 // is known to not change the value of Y. ----
4701 // We can only expand it into libcall if the TRUNC is 0. ----
4702 bool IsStrict = Node->isStrictFPOpcode(); 0
4703 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(IsStrict ? 1 : 0); 0
4704 SDValue Chain = IsStrict ? Node->getOperand(0) : SDValue(); 0
4705 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0); 0
4706 assert(cast(Node->getOperand(IsStrict ? 2 : 1))->isZero() && 0
4707 "Unable to expand as libcall if it is not normal rounding"); ----
4708 ----
4709 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::getFPROUND(Op.getValueType(), VT); 0
4710 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Unable to legalize as libcall"); 0
4711 ----
4712 TargetLowering::MakeLibCallOptions CallOptions; 0
4713 std::pair Tmp = ----
4714 TLI.makeLibCall(DAG, LC, VT, Op, CallOptions, SDLoc(Node), Chain); 0
4715 Results.push_back(Tmp.first); 0
4716 if (IsStrict) 0
4717 Results.push_back(Tmp.second); 0
4718 break; 0
4719 } ----
4720 case ISD::FP_EXTEND: { 0
4721 Results.push_back( 0
4722 ExpandLibCall(RTLIB::getFPEXT(Node->getOperand(0).getValueType(), 0
4723 Node->getValueType(0)), ----
4724 Node, false).first); ----
4725 break; 0
4726 } ----
4727 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND: 0
4728 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_FP16: { ----
4729 RTLIB::Libcall LC = ----
4730 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_FP16 0

4736 TargetLowering::MakeLibCallOptions CallOptions; 0

4741 Results.push_back(Tmp.second); 0

4743 } ----
4744 case ISD::FSUB: 0

4747 RTLIB::SUB_F80, RTLIB::SUB_F128, ----
4748 RTLIB::SUB_PPCF128, Results); ----
4749 break; 0
4750 case ISD::SREM: 0
4751 Results.push_back(ExpandIntLibCall(Node, true, 0

4754 RTLIB::SREM_I64, RTLIB::SREM_I128)); ----

4756 case ISD::UREM: 0
4757 Results.push_back(ExpandIntLibCall(Node, false, 0

4759 RTLIB::UREM_I16, RTLIB::UREM_I32, ----
4760 RTLIB::UREM_I64, RTLIB::UREM_I128)); ----
4761 break; 0
4762 case ISD::SDIV: 0

4768 case ISD::UDIV: 0
