4772 RTLIB::UDIV_I64, RTLIB::UDIV_I128)); ----
4773 break; 0
4774 case ISD::SDIVREM: 0
4775 case ISD::UDIVREM: ----
4776 // Expand into divrem libcall ----
4777 ExpandDivRemLibCall(Node, Results); 0
4778 break; 0
4779 case ISD::MUL: 0
4780 Results.push_back(ExpandIntLibCall(Node, false, 0
4781 RTLIB::MUL_I8, ----
4782 RTLIB::MUL_I16, RTLIB::MUL_I32, ----
4783 RTLIB::MUL_I64, RTLIB::MUL_I128)); ----
4784 break; 0
4785 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF: 0
4786 switch (Node->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) { 0
4787 default: 0
4788 llvm_unreachable("LibCall explicitly requested, but not available"); 0
4789 case MVT::i32: 0
4790 Results.push_back(ExpandLibCall(RTLIB::CTLZ_I32, Node, false).first); 0
4791 break; 0
4792 case MVT::i64: 0
4793 Results.push_back(ExpandLibCall(RTLIB::CTLZ_I64, Node, false).first); 0
4794 break; 0
4795 case MVT::i128: 0
4796 Results.push_back(ExpandLibCall(RTLIB::CTLZ_I128, Node, false).first); 0
4797 break; 0
4798 } ----
4799 break; 0
4800 case ISD::RESET_FPENV: { 0
4801 // It is legalized to call 'fesetenv(FE_DFL_ENV)'. On most targets ----
4802 // FE_DFL_ENV is defined as '((const fenv_t *) -1)' in glibc. ----
4803 SDValue Ptr = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(-1LL, dl); 0
4804 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); 0
4805 Results.push_back( 0
4806 DAG.makeStateFunctionCall(RTLIB::FESETENV, Ptr, Chain, dl)); 0
4807 break; 0
4808 } ----
4809 case ISD::GET_FPENV_MEM: { 0
4810 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); 0
4811 SDValue EnvPtr = Node->getOperand(1); 0
4812 Results.push_back( 0
4813 DAG.makeStateFunctionCall(RTLIB::FEGETENV, EnvPtr, Chain, dl)); 0
4814 break; 0
4815 } ----
4816 case ISD::SET_FPENV_MEM: { 0
4817 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); 0
4818 SDValue EnvPtr = Node->getOperand(1); 0
4819 Results.push_back( 0
4820 DAG.makeStateFunctionCall(RTLIB::FESETENV, EnvPtr, Chain, dl)); 0
4821 break; 0
4822 } ----
4823 } ----
4824 ----
4825 // Replace the original node with the legalized result. ----
4826 if (!Results.empty()) { 0
4827 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully converted node to libcall\n"); 0
4828 ReplaceNode(Node, Results.data()); 0
4829 } else ----
4830 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Could not convert node to libcall\n"); 0
4831 } 0
4832 ----
4833 // Determine the vector type to use in place of an original scalar element when ----
4834 // promoting equally sized vectors. ----
4835 static MVT getPromotedVectorElementType(const TargetLowering &TLI, 0
4836 MVT EltVT, MVT NewEltVT) { ----
4837 unsigned OldEltsPerNewElt = EltVT.getSizeInBits() / NewEltVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
4838 MVT MidVT = MVT::getVectorVT(NewEltVT, OldEltsPerNewElt); 0
4839 assert(TLI.isTypeLegal(MidVT) && "unexpected"); 0
4840 return MidVT; 0
4841 } ----
4842 ----
4843 void SelectionDAGLegalize::PromoteNode(SDNode *Node) { 0
4844 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying to promote node\n"); 0
4845 SmallVector Results; 0
4846 MVT OVT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
4847 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UINT_TO_FP || 0
4848 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SINT_TO_FP || 0
4849 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC || 0
4850 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT || 0
4851 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT) { 0
4852 OVT = Node->getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType(); 0
4853 } ----
4854 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP || 0
4855 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP || 0
4856 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FSETCC || 0
4857 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS) 0
4858 OVT = Node->getOperand(1).getSimpleValueType(); 0
4859 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::BR_CC || 0
4860 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SELECT_CC) 0
4861 OVT = Node->getOperand(2).getSimpleValueType(); 0
4862 MVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToPromoteTo(Node->getOpcode(), OVT); 0
4863 SDLoc dl(Node); 0
4864 SDValue Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4; 0
4865 switch (Node->getOpcode()) { 0
4866 case ISD::CTTZ: 0
4867 case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF: ----
4868 case ISD::CTLZ: ----
4869 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF: ----
4870 case ISD::CTPOP: ----
4871 // Zero extend the argument unless its cttz, then use any_extend. ----
4872 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ || 0
4873 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF) 0
4874 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
4875 else ----
4876 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
4877 ----
4878 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ) { 0
4879 // The count is the same in the promoted type except if the original ----
4880 // value was zero. This can be handled by setting the bit just off ----
4881 // the top of the original type. ----
4882 auto TopBit = APInt::getOneBitSet(NVT.getSizeInBits(), 0
4883 OVT.getSizeInBits()); 0
4884 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Tmp1, 0
4885 DAG.getConstant(TopBit, dl, NVT)); 0
4886 } 0
4887 // Perform the larger operation. For CTPOP and CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, this is ----
4888 // already the correct result. ----
4889 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1); 0
4890 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTLZ || 0
4891 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF) { 0
4892 // Tmp1 = Tmp1 - (sizeinbits(NVT) - sizeinbits(Old VT)) ----
4893 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, NVT, Tmp1, 0
4894 DAG.getConstant(NVT.getSizeInBits() - 0
4895 OVT.getSizeInBits(), dl, NVT)); 0
4896 } ----
4897 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, OVT, Tmp1)); 0
4898 break; 0
4899 case ISD::BITREVERSE: 0
4900 case ISD::BSWAP: { ----
4901 unsigned DiffBits = NVT.getSizeInBits() - OVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
4902 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
4903 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1); 0
4904 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode( 0
4905 ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, Tmp1, ----
4906 DAG.getConstant(DiffBits, dl, 0
4907 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(NVT, DAG.getDataLayout()))); 0
4908 ----
4909 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, OVT, Tmp1)); 0
4910 break; 0
4911 } ----
4912 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT: 0
4913 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_UINT: ----
4914 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT: ----
4915 case ISD::STRICT_FP_TO_SINT: ----
4916 PromoteLegalFP_TO_INT(Node, dl, Results); 0
4917 break; 0
4918 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT_SAT: 0
4919 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT_SAT: ----
4920 Results.push_back(PromoteLegalFP_TO_INT_SAT(Node, dl)); 0
4921 break; 0
4922 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP: 0
4923 case ISD::STRICT_UINT_TO_FP: ----
4924 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP: ----
4925 case ISD::STRICT_SINT_TO_FP: ----
4926 PromoteLegalINT_TO_FP(Node, dl, Results); 0
4927 break; 0
4928 case ISD::VAARG: { 0
4929 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); // Get the chain. 0
4930 SDValue Ptr = Node->getOperand(1); // Get the pointer. 0
4931 ----
4932 unsigned TruncOp; ----
4933 if (OVT.isVector()) { 0
4934 TruncOp = ISD::BITCAST; 0
4935 } else { ----
4936 assert(OVT.isInteger() 0
4937 && "VAARG promotion is supported only for vectors or integer types"); ----
4938 TruncOp = ISD::TRUNCATE; 0
4939 } ----
4940 ----
4941 // Perform the larger operation, then convert back ----
4942 Tmp1 = DAG.getVAArg(NVT, dl, Chain, Ptr, Node->getOperand(2), 0
4943 Node->getConstantOperandVal(3)); 0
4944 Chain = Tmp1.getValue(1); 0
4945 ----
4946 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(TruncOp, dl, OVT, Tmp1); 0
4947 ----
4948 // Modified the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to ----
4949 // use the new one. ----
4950 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 0), Tmp2); 0
4951 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 1), Chain); 0
4952 if (UpdatedNodes) { 0
4953 UpdatedNodes->insert(Tmp2.getNode()); 0
4954 UpdatedNodes->insert(Chain.getNode()); 0
4955 } ----
4956 ReplacedNode(Node); 0
4957 break; 0
4958 } ----
4959 case ISD::MUL: 0
4960 case ISD::SDIV: ----
4961 case ISD::SREM: ----
4962 case ISD::UDIV: ----
4963 case ISD::UREM: ----
4964 case ISD::AND: ----
4965 case ISD::OR: ----
4966 case ISD::XOR: { ----
4967 unsigned ExtOp, TruncOp; ----
4968 if (OVT.isVector()) { 0
4969 ExtOp = ISD::BITCAST; 0
4970 TruncOp = ISD::BITCAST; 0
4971 } else { ----
4972 assert(OVT.isInteger() && "Cannot promote logic operation"); 0
4973 ----
4974 switch (Node->getOpcode()) { 0
4975 default: 0

4977 break; 0
4978 case ISD::SDIV: 0

4980 ExtOp = ISD::SIGN_EXTEND; 0

4982 case ISD::UDIV: 0
4983 case ISD::UREM: ----
4984 ExtOp = ISD::ZERO_EXTEND; 0
4985 break; 0
4986 } ----
4987 TruncOp = ISD::TRUNCATE; 0

4989 // Promote each of the values to the new type. ----
4990 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
4991 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1)); 0
4992 // Perform the larger operation, then convert back ----
4993 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2); 0
4994 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(TruncOp, dl, OVT, Tmp1)); 0
4995 break; 0
4996 } ----
4997 case ISD::UMUL_LOHI: 0
4998 case ISD::SMUL_LOHI: { ----
4999 // Promote to a multiply in a wider integer type. ----
5000 unsigned ExtOp = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UMUL_LOHI ? ISD::ZERO_EXTEND 0
5001 : ISD::SIGN_EXTEND; 0
5002 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0)); 0
5003 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1)); 0
5004 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2); 0

5012 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, OVT, Tmp2)); 0

5014 } ----
5015 case ISD::SELECT: { 0
5016 unsigned ExtOp, TruncOp; ----
5017 if (Node->getValueType(0).isVector() || 0

5019 ExtOp = ISD::BITCAST; 0
5020 TruncOp = ISD::BITCAST; 0
5021 } else if (Node->getValueType(0).isInteger()) { 0
5022 ExtOp = ISD::ANY_EXTEND; 0
5023 TruncOp = ISD::TRUNCATE; 0
5024 } else { ----
5025 ExtOp = ISD::FP_EXTEND; 0
5026 TruncOp = ISD::FP_ROUND; 0
5027 } ----
5028 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0); 0

5102 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCC: ----
5103 case ISD::STRICT_FSETCCS: { ----

5294 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: { 0
5295 MVT EltVT = OVT.getVectorElementType(); 0
5296 MVT NewEltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType(); 0
5297 ----
5298 // Handle bitcasts to a different vector type with the same total bit size ----
5299 // ----
5300 // e.g. v2i64 = build_vector i64:x, i64:y => v4i32 ----
5301 // => ----
5302 // v4i32 = concat_vectors (v2i32 (bitcast i64:x)), (v2i32 (bitcast i64:y)) ----
5303 ----
5304 assert(NVT.isVector() && OVT.getSizeInBits() == NVT.getSizeInBits() && 0
5305 "Invalid promote type for build_vector"); ----
5306 assert(NewEltVT.bitsLT(EltVT) && "not handled"); 0
5307 ----
5308 MVT MidVT = getPromotedVectorElementType(TLI, EltVT, NewEltVT); 0
5309 ----
5310 SmallVector NewOps; 0
5311 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Node->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) { 0
5312 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(I); 0
5313 NewOps.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(Op), MidVT, Op)); 0
5314 } ----
